title: homestyle baked beans
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine chopped onion, pork and beans, brown sugar and mustard.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with desired amount of bacon before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yamasitti
directions: Chop canned (or cooked) hamburg until it is fine.
Place a layer in baking dish.
Now put on a layer of macaroni.
Cut cheese and layer over macaroni.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over all and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
A little milk may be added if it seems too dry.

title: apple salad
directions: Chop together apples, celery and nuts.
Add dressing made of vinegar, eggs, sugar and sour cream.
Let it come to a boil.
When cool, mix with apples, celery and nuts.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms in salt water.
Fry sausage in skillet; add salt, onion and a dash of garlic.
Cut up mushroom stems and fry along with sausage; add cheese.
Stuff mushrooms with filling ingredients; bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl, but adding soda to the cup
of
hot water before putting in large bowl.
I don't make mixture real stiff so I chill it, then take out of fridge only what I roll out each time.	Cookies are moist and soft.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add celery and onion; saute briefly.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce(serves 50)
directions: Brown beef; add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1/2 hour or until thickened.
Cook 4 pounds spaghetti as directed on box.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until creamy.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat mixture until sugar is dissolved. Stir in crumbled biscuits until well moistened.
Turn mixture into lightly buttered 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes or until top is brown and mixture is set.
Serve with heavy cream, whipped cream or plain.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: daddy's best pancakes
directions: Heat skillet to 370°.
Stir up ingredients lightly.
Drop in skillet; cook.
Can freeze and then drop in toaster to heat.

title: meatballs lasagna style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine meat, egg, onion and pepper.
Mix to blend.
Shape into small balls.
Place meatballs in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Spoon cottage cheese around meatballs and spoon sauce over all.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: eggplant bake
directions: Combine and pour into greased casserole pan and bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach (small leaves).
Fry bacon and drain. Add scallions, pepper, sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour boiling mixture over spinach.
Add eggs and bacon.
Toss well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until fluffy. Add eggs and mix well. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition. Stir in flavorings. Spoon into 10-inch greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: neato chicken nuggets with dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
In medium bowl, blend ketchup, honey and mustard.
Remove 1/2 cup of the sauce mixture to be used later for dipping.
Cover and refrigerate.
Place chicken in remaining sauce mixture and using a fork, toss until coated.
In medium bowl, combine cornmeal and melted butter until blended.
Stir in flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time, tossing until coated with cornmeal mixture.
Arrange nuggets in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until fully cooked.
Cool slightly and refrigerate if packing in lunch box.
Serve with dipping sauce.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in a double boiler.
Stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Drop onto wax paper.
Refrigerate.
They harden fast.

title: shrimp caratoni
directions: Saute garlic in butter or olive oil for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and half the basil and saute for an additional minute. Cover and remove from the heat.
In a separate large mixing bowl, add remaining basil, anchovy paste, Pesto sauce, crushed fennel seed and heavy cream.
Cook pasta to degree of preference, drain and add immediately to mixing bowl.
Toss pasta to gain thorough coating of ingredients.
Add sauteed ingredients and shrimp and toss again.
Serve immediately with a covering of fresh grated Romano cheese.

title: honey chicken nuggets
directions: You will need Reynolds Cut Rite wax paper.
In a small bowl, beat together egg and milk.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; dip in egg mixture.
Place crushed chips on a sheet of wax paper.
Dip chicken in crushed chips, turning to coat evenly.
Place coated chicken in microwave safe platter; sprinkle with remaining crushed chips.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on Medium-high power until chicken is tender, 4 to 6 minutes.
Serve immediately with honey.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot brie cheese
directions: Place Brie in a 10-inch quiche dish.
Spread chutney center outward, not quite to the edge.
Cover with cooked bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Bremmer wafers.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; beat.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in a 15 x 10-inch floured and greased pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Test; it may take a little longer.

title: dark red punch
directions: Mix all together and float anything light colored in it.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate and bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minuets.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: trudi's green pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving sizes.
Roll meat in flour and brown in hot skillet with cooking oil in it.
Transfer meat into crock-pot or roaster.
If using a crock-pot, put meat and onion on bottom.
Cut green peppers into strips and cover meat with it. Pour 1 can tomato soup, diluted with 3/4 can water, over peppers. Put any optional choices in crock-pot.
Put on low setting for about 5 to 6 hours.
Test for doneness.
The meat can be roasted in an oven for about 1 hour at 350°.
Test to see if it is done. Serve with rice or noodles.
Increase cooking time if more meat is used.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Prepare finely chopped nuts. Mix nuts, shortening, butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in flour and baking powder (sifted together).
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Beat egg white slightly and dip and roll balls in the finely chopped nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 5 minutes at 375°.
Press thumb into top of each cookie. Return to oven for 8 minutes longer.
When cool, fill with jelly, tinted frosting or a red cherry.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: deluxe buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry ingredients and mix well.

title: cheddar chicken
directions: Simmer breasts in water with onions and celery tops.
Strain off broth and keep.
Cool chicken and cut into chunks.
Meanwhile, cook rice.
Turn into greased casserole.
Sprinkle rice with cheese.
Cover with chicken and sprinkle with nuts.
Pour over soup that was thinned with stock.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually, then salt and vanilla. Stir in evaporated milk and Coffee Rich.
Peel and chop peaches, then partially mash peaches.
Add to cream mixture.
Follow directions of electric freezer for freezing ice cream.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and cut unpeeled zucchini and peel onions.
Cut in very thin slices and place in large pot.
Cover with water and add salt.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over zucchini and onions.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; rub in the shortening and mix to a light dough with the egg and milk.
Roll out on a floured board, cut into biscuits and bake about 15 minutes in a hot oven.

title: turtle cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into and up the sides of 9-inch spring-form pan the cookie crumbs with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Sift together flour and salt. Cut in shortening.
Add sufficient cold water gradually to make a dough. Divide dough in thirds.
Roll out on a lightly floured board to a rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread each rectangle with sausage.
Roll up into a roll. Chill a couple of hours or overnight.
Slice 1/3-inch thick and bake at 400°.
Serve with coffee.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Break up sausage and fry to light brown.
Remove from skillet and pour off, except 2 or 3 tablespoons fat.
Cook onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Add sausage and tomato soup.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add crushed pineapple and coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake until firm at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: garbanzo rice chili soup
directions: Cut meat in chunks and brown in oil. Saute onion and bell pepper with meat till tender. Add all other ingredients and cook for 1 hour.

title: apples with pork chops
directions: Place apples in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle on sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Place the pork chops on top, which have been browned. Cover and bake in a 400° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy peanut butter frosting
directions: In a small saucepan gradually stir milk into flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Transfer to small mixer bowl; press plastic wrap directly on surface.
Cool to room temperature, about 1/2 hour.
Add sugar, peanut butter, shortening, vanilla and salt.
Beat on high speed of electric mixer until mixture becomes fluffy and sugar is completely dissolved.
Makes about 3 cups frosting.

title: cheesy garlic croutons(go with lemon caesar salad)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Spread cubes in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, combine margarine and garlic powder; mix well.
Drizzle margarine mixture over cubes; toss to coat. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes or until dry, crisp and golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: sherry cake
directions: Mix and put in tube or Bundt pan which has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's pickle beets
directions: Prepare beets and cook until tender enough to stick a fork in easily.
Fill quart jars with beets.
Now heat vinegar, water and sugar; boil 10 minutes.
Put 1 teaspoon pickling spice on top of beets in each jar.
Pour boiling vinegar mixture to cover beets. Seal immediately.

title: jiffy corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix hot water, jello, pineapple juice and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator and let congeal a little.
Remove from refrigerator, add rest of ingredients.
(Whip the whipping cream before adding.)
Mold and serve on lettuce.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and bell peppers in large bowl.
Put in 2-quart pan with lid.

title: blue ribbon carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir into flour mixture with carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts. Pour into prepared pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Serve with additional cheese if you wish.

title: meat loaf
directions: I just use the ground beef, but the recipe called for both. Mix all the ingredients and bake at 350° for about an hour.
The last 5 to 10 minutes, cover the loaf with sauce.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until almost tender. Add mushrooms and cook lightly. Blend in flour and marjoram.
Add beef broth all at once. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat. Stir in wine and parsley.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Serves 6.
Great with steak!

title: date muffins
directions: Cut dates up fine, add to the boiling water.
Add oleo and stir good until oleo is melted.
Add soda; stir lightly.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Mash date mixture until dates are a mush.
Add eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Stir and add the nuts.
Mix good and add the flour.

title: cheese blitzs
directions: Roll bread flat with rolling pin.
Combine cream cheese, sugar with cinnamon and egg yolk.
Spread on each piece of bread.
Roll up and cut in half.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Roll each piece in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen to bake later.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into small chunks.
Cook stuffing as directed.
Mix chicken and Miracle Whip with stuffing and fill shells.
Mix 4 cans of soup with 3 cans of water.
Place half of soup in pan and then place stuffed shells in pan.
Pour remaining soup over shells.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 8-inch baking dish. Mix all ingredients in order listed, except cheese.
Pour half the batter into prepared pan.
Top with half the cheese.
Add the rest of the batter and cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chili
directions: Melt lard in deep pan.
Add meat and cook slowly until slightly browned.
Add onion, garlic, water, chili powder, tomatoes and salt.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Before serving, add the beans and cook long enough to heat beans thoroughly.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 53 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: german homemade bread
directions: Raise for 2 hours in bowl.
Rework dough; form into loaves. Let set for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour ("crusty").
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan delights
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add water and vanilla.
Fold in flour and add nuts.
Pinch off in small amounts and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.
Remove from cookie sheet as soon as taken from oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash potatoes well until smooth.
Stir in milk, molasses, brown sugar, butter, eggs and cinnamon.
Spoon mixture into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients, except cheeses and paprika, into 8-inch round glass baking dish.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove wrap and stir.
Cover and cook 4 minutes more.
Combine cheese and paprika; sprinkle over potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: christmas tree ornaments
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead dough 5 to 10 minutes. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness. Use Christmas cookie cutters and cut to desired shapes.
Make a hole in each to put hanger through.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Paint or varnish.
This can also be used to model magnetic ornaments.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Knead dough together.
Roll out pieces into a long snake then form into a pretzel shape.
Bake 425 degrees until lightly browned.
Don't overbake.
You can top with
large grain salt.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix first four ingredients to make a pie crust; press into bottom (only) of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers; cook in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat, add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes. Arrange peppers in pan (ungreased); salt and pepper lightly.
Stuff peppers with rest of mixture.
Pour about 1 tablespoon tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: smoky cheese ball
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, shredded Cheddar cheese, softened butter, milk and steak sauce.
Beat mixture with electric mixer until fluffy.
Chill slightly; shape into a ball. Place chopped nuts on waxed paper; gently roll cheese ball over nuts to coat.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: rotini fruit salad
directions: Cook rotini according to directions on the package, then drain and rinse several times with cold water.
Drain again.
Combine cooled rotini, pineapple chunks, grapes, coconut and slivered almonds.
Toss with the yogurt.
Add mandarin oranges, strawberries and kiwi.
Toss, then chill 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add pineapple juice and allow to cool. Add cream.
Chill in refrigerator until the mixture reaches the mushy stage. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into molds and refrigerate until set.
(This salad is good for serving with barbecued chicken and baked potatoes.)

title: easy french bread
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast into 1/2 cup of warm water.
Stir until yeast has dissolved.
Put the sugar, salt and shortening into a large bowl.
Add remaining cup of very warm water and stir until dissolved.
Add yeast mixture.
Add the 4 cups of flour and mix well, then stir through this dough with a spoon at 10-minute intervals five times.
(No kneading necessary.)
Next, have a lightly floured board and turn the dough onto it.
Cut the dough in half and shape into two balls.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
One hour's time in all, up to now.
Use rolling pin, roll each ball into a rectangle about 10 x 8-inches.
Using fingers, start rolling on the long side and roll tightly like a jelly roll.
Seal the edge of the dough by pinching together and place these 2 long rolls on a greased cookie sheet side by side.
Slash top of each roll diagonally six times.
Cover with a towel and allow to rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush tops of baked loaves with butter.

title: cherry salad
directions: Pour pie filling and milk in large bowl and add pineapple, pecans, cottage cheese and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip, then bananas, if desired.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: 7-up biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Flour dough board with Bisquick; roll dough out and cut out biscuits.
Melt 1/2 stick butter or margarine.
Drizzle over cut out biscuits and place in greased pan.
Bake at 425° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: sharon's tomato sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and butter for 15 minutes.
Run through foley mill.
Add onion, salt and sugar.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes.
Put in pint containers and freeze.
Makes 1 quart.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 13 x 9-inch (glass preferred), melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour sweetened, condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with chips, then coconut and nuts; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: diabetic sugarless apple cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine dates, apple, raisins and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda.
Stir into cooled apple mixture and mix well.
Combine egg and sweetener; add to batter.
Drop by teaspoonful onto nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: orange yogurt freeze
directions: Drain oranges.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar and gelatin.
Stir in orange juice.
Heat and stir until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Place oranges, gelatin mixture, yogurt and vanilla in a blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Fold into yogurt mixture, then transfer to an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf dish.
Cover and freeze 3 to 24 hours or until firm.
Serve in dessert dishes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, condensed milk and butter in a large saucepan; cool slightly.
Fold in peanuts, vanilla and marshmallows.
Spread mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool for 4 to 6 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only
of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper.
Beat egg slightly; stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Your cumin powder and salt is what makes the taste, while cooking taste.
You may want to add more salt and cumin powder.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Blend butter, sugar and water in a heavy frypan over low heat. Add carrots.
Cook over low heat to coat all sides with syrup. Keep heat low to prevent scorching.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Spread frozen rolls on cookie sheet to thaw, then roll the rolls into the melted butter, then roll into sugar and cinnamon mix.
Place in Bundt pan.
Let rise and bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add soups and olives; cook until melted.
Spoon into bowl.
Layer picante sauce on top.
Serve warm with nacho chips.
Spoon over or dip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake in bite size pieces; set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, milk and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix strawberries and pie mix.
Layer cake pieces, Cool Whip mix and strawberry mix in punch bowl, ending with cake.
Spread strawberry glaze over top.
Chill several hours.

title: cream cheese and picante sauce
directions: Mash with fork and dip with big chips.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart casserole (can use whole head or you can cut cauliflower up); add water.
Cook, covered, 8 to 9 minutes on High in microwave or until tender.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and onion.
Spoon over cauliflower; sprinkle with cheese. Microwave uncovered for 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spam burger
directions: Slice Spam meat into 3 to 6 square slices.
Grill, pan-fry or broil until lightly browned.
Serve on bun with lettuce, tomato, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add your favorite condiments.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients.
Add oranges.
Pour in glass dish and refrigerate.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, butter, cheese and scallions until smooth.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch glass pan with Pam or line with butter.
Place potatoes in pan.
Top with soup mixture; sprinkle with bread crumbs and bits of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add vegetable, if desired.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Mix everything except ice cream, then stir in ice cream and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water, butter and salt until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Add flour all at once.
Mix with wooden spoon vigorously until mixture forms a ball.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition until mixture is smooth.
Drop batter into greased baking sheet using tablespoon. Cool; add pudding and sprinkle
powdered sugar.

title: three bean salad
directions: Put first 3 ingredients together and drain.
Then mix together the rest of the ingredients.
After you mix, then add this to the 3 bean mixture and stir to coat the beans.
Store overnight in the refrigerator or make 3 or 4 hours ahead of time.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Break up lettuce; spread mayonnaise on it.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Layer the rest of ingredients.
Cover and chill for 3 hours.
Serves 12.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Add egg and next 3 ingredients; mix well. In a skillet, heat vegetable oil on medium-high. Spoon mixture into skillet. Turn when golden brown. When brown on all sides, drain on paper towel.

title: stuffed french rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add soup, simmer until most of the juice is gone.
Stuff rolls.
Bake until crisp.

title: penuchi cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine margarine, brown sugar or
cocoa (fudge cookies), sugar and milk.
Bring to boil slowly; stir constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter. Stir until thick enough to drop from spoon.
Drop onto wax paper and allow to cool and harden.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Combine soup, milk, rice, onion, mayonnaise, egg and croutons. Mix well. Add cooked broccoli and mix well. Melt cheese and margarine in double boiler.
Layer the broccoli mixture and cheese mixture in a greased casserole, ending with cheese mixture. Spread crackers on top. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cabbage fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Mix cabbage, pineapple, grapes, almonds and celery.
For dressing, mix the yogurt with juice.
Add sweetener.
Dressing will be tangy-sweet.
Pour over salad and toss.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Then add, but do not mix in, the milk and butter.
Cook in microwave oven for 3 1/2 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix milk, cream of tartar and baking soda until foamy.
Mix all together.
Add flour. Drop by teaspoon.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything (except potato chips) together.
Put in baking dish and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate mint cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and salt.
Sift together cocoa and sugar.
Mix together and put three holes in mixture.

title: rose's zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Put flour in until thick.
Mix all together and put in baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: golden eggnog
directions: Whip egg whites until foamy; add slowly sugar while beating. Beat only until peaks are soft and shiny.
Beat yolks until thick, then add to whites.
Slowly stir in milk and vanilla; fold whipped cream into egg mixture. Chill.
Serve in a chilled bowl; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 24.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric beater on low or by hand.
Serve with cut-up chunks of fruit around bowl of dip.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Especially good over boiled weiners.
I pour sauce over them and bake uncovered about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed fruit melba dessert
directions: Cook puddings and fruit juice until thick; cool.
In a large bowl, combine mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks and sliced banana.
Pour the sauce over the fruit.
Mix all together.
After 1/2 hour, mix again.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: homemade play dough
directions: In a saucepan, combine salt and water.
Heat over medium heat until ingredients come to a boil. Stir frequently, almost continuously.
Remove from heat.
Add alum, salad oil and drops of food coloring.
Mix together.
Add flour, kneading until play dough consistency is achieved. Does not need to be refrigerated.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges together.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Mix instant vanilla pudding and pineapple together thoroughly in mixer.
Add whipped topping.
Frost when cake has cooled.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in half to make winglets.
Marinate overnight, shaking jar occasionally.
Drain and cook chicken in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Turn chicken once. Recipe may be doubled.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat in pan with onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir together well and heat thoroughly.
Takes about 1/2 hour to make. Is a quick, delicious, low-fat meal.
Serve with taco chips, crackers or top with grated cheese.

title: spiced melon rind
directions: Let watermelon rind stand in salted water to cover overnight. Next day, drain and cover with fresh cold water.
Cook until tender, about 10 minutes, then drain.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes approximately 45 minutes on medium heat or until soft.
Peel potatoes and place in refrigerator for about 5 minutes.
Remove potatoes when cool and cut into quarters; then cut them into cubes, into a medium size serving bowl.
Mix ingredients well with potatoes, using only 2 boiled eggs.
When ingredients are mixed well, smooth over top.
Slice remaining boiled egg for decoration; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: sheboygan brats
directions: Fill a pot halfway with beer, water and sliced onion.
Bring to a boil.
Plunge in sausages and simmer 20 minutes.
If any sausages rise to surface while simmering, prick with a sharp knife.
As sausages simmer, melt butter in skillet and saute diced onions until golden brown.
Set aside.
Remove sausages from water and cook on grill until crusty brown.
Serve with sauteed onions.

title: cherry cool whip salad
directions: Gently mix cottage cheese and dry jello together until well mixed.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Very gently, mix in Cool Whip.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
You can substitute fruit cocktail for pineapple.

title: beef delight
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in oil in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add macaroni and saute until browned.
Add ground beef mixture, soup and 1 soup can of water, mixing well.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender, adding additional water if necessary.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: u.s.d.a.  pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until just blended.
Add sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Add cooled butter and vanilla, mixing just to blend.
Spread nuts in bottom of pie shell.
Pour in filling.
Place pie in oven.
Reduce heat to 325° at once.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, flour and spices.
Coat berries with sugar mixture.
Place mixture in a shallow 8 1/2-inch round casserole dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Drain clams (reserve liquid and set aside). In skillet, slowly heat oil and butter. Add garlic and saute until golden.
Remove from heat.
Stir in clam liquid, parsley and salt, bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add clams and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.

title: easy fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients on stove until bubbly on high heat. Reduce to medium heat and cook
5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in buttered dish and cool.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Bread for dressing should be at least 1 day old.
Break bread into small pieces in a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour broth over mixture until you have a thick mixture while stirring.
Pour into a baking pan or dish and bake until lightly brown.

title: real red devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 layer pans, 8 or 9 1/2-inch.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting. Blend in bowl flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add shortening and 2/3 cup milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add rest of milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl frequently.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth; add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Place ball on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
May be baked in the ball.
Push Hershey's Kiss into cookie as soon as it is done baking.

title: luscious lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add Mountain Dew.
Stir in marshmallows, pineapple and 1/2 of the pie filling.
Pour into a 2-quart oblong pan or salad bowl until set.
Fold in topping and remaining pie filling and spread on top.

title: no peek chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, water, parsley and rice together.
Pour into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Lay uncooked chicken breasts over rice mixture.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
No peeking until ready to come out of the oven.
Whole fryer or chicken parts can be substituted for breasts.

title: old boston sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add sour cream.
Mix only until blended.
Turn onto lightly floured board or tabletop and knead lightly for about 30 seconds.
Pat into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch rounds with floured biscuit cutter or the top of a drinking glass.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 15 minutes.
You may brush melted butter on tops before baking to get a browner crust.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add brown sugar, oatmeal and pecans.
Mix.
Add margarine, blending with a fork.
Press half of mixture into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread jam over mixture.
Cover jam with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.
May be made a day ahead and left in refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients with a dash of black pepper; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 or 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 8.

title: cheese loaf ring with peas
directions: Cook milk, vinegar and eggs in top of double boiler until light in color.
Pour over cheese, pimento and cracker crumbs. Mix well.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: You will need a cookie pan and Pam spray.

title: easy lemon cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients; spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat 2 minutes on medium speed with electric mixer.
Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and invert onto cake platter.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and corn syrup for 5 minutes, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Add salt, soda and butter flavoring.
Mix with corn.
Place on cookie sheets; put into a 200° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir every 5 to 10 minutes to keep from burning.
Cool and eat.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mash tomatoes.
Put the rice in a greased casserole dish; cover with the mashed tomatoes.
Place the sausages on top and pour the liquid over the tomatoes and rice.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg rolls
directions: Heat oil and stir-fry chicken and vegetables for 3 or 4 minutes.
Season with soy sauce and salt.
Put about 2 tablespoons of filling mixture on each wrapper.
Roll according to directions on wrapper package.
Fry in small amount of oil in skillet until golden; drain.
Serve with Aunt Betty's hot mustard.

title: judi's salad
directions: Layer ingredients in container in order given.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat until creamy.
Sprinkle cake with nuts.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in boiling water (1 teaspoon salt) 14 minutes. Spread in bottom of large casserole dish. Place raw pork chops on top. Salt and pepper chops. Spoon half the mushroom soup over. Add water to remaining soup to fill can. Stir well and pour over dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered. Serves 6.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a shallow 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine all ingredients except shrimp.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir shrimp into butter sauce.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until shrimp are opaque.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 5 minutes before serving.
(Can be served over pasta or with rice.)
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Make up each color of Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water in separate pans.
Allow to jell in thin layer.
Mix sugar, crushed graham crackers and butter.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture. Reserve 1/3 for topping.
Dissolve plain gelatin in cold water. Add hot pineapple juice.
Let stand until syrupy.
Fold Cool Whip into pineapple mixture.
Cut Jell-O into squares and fold into pineapple-cream mixture.
Pour into pan lined with graham cracker mixture.
Refrigerate for 6 to 12 hours.

title: fennel bread sticks
directions: Mix dry yeast with 2 cups flour in a large bowl; stir in fennel seeds.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: Prepare pudding by mixing pudding mix and milk. Stir until all lumps are gone and pudding is smooth. Pour immediately into pie crust. Set in refrigerator and chill for at least 30 minutes. When pie is chilled, add thawed Cool Whip to top of pie, spreading evenly to edges.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift with sugar and salt.
Heat water, cocoa and margarine until it boils.
Add to flour mixture and stir well.
Beat eggs, add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and then add to flour, cocoa mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (or cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so.
Frost.

title: bread starter or emptyings
directions: Mix ingredients until it's a smooth paste.
Pour into crockery pitcher and leave 3 or 4 days until it's slightly sour and solidifies (clabbers).
Emptyings may be replenished after use by saving a piece of the dough to put back in pitcher along with leftover scrapings.
More buttermilk or milk may be added as needed.

title: make your own rondele
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend all ingredients and chill.
Yield: 1 cup.
Takes 5 minutes to prepare.
tags: Knorr Swiss aromat seasoning for meat

title: polenta chicken corn meal mush
directions: Saute the chicken until golden brown in the butter and oil, about 10 minutes.
Then add the chopped onion, carrots, celery, mushrooms and cook 5 minutes until the onions are wilted.
Then add the tomatoes and the wine.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
When chicken is tender, place on a hot platter.
Strain sauce; season to taste, heat and pour over chicken.
May top with fresh mushrooms sauteed in butter and serve with polenta.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Add sugar, butter, salt, syrup and cream to chocolate squares.
Boil 5 minutes.
Simmer, uncovered, slowly, stirring constantly, to form a ball stage or to 240°.
Remove from heat; add flavoring.
Pour into buttered pan, 6 x 10.
Cool.
Best when left overnight.
Cut into 3/4-inch squares.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat the cake mix, oil, eggs and milk 2 minutes. Add icing to batter and mix gently. Spray tube pan. Place pecans in the bottom of the pan, then add the batter. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Let set for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and allow to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes a nice large casserole.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir together all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture; mix well.
Shape dough in long rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper; refrigerate or freeze.
Chill thoroughly, preferably overnight.
Cut into thin slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Dough may be kept in freezer for several weeks.

title: hot! sauce
directions: Combine lime juice, vinegar and sliced carrots in blender. Liquefy.
Add salt, water and sliced peppers.
Liquefy again. Pour mixture into saucepan and bring to boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Transfer to a bottle and keep refrigerated.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut off the stem ends and slice the tomatoes in thick slices. Press each slice in the flour, coating it heavily.
In a frying pan, heat the bacon fat and oil.
Add the tomatoes.
While the tomatoes are browning on one side, sprinkle the brown sugar liberally on the other side.
Turn over carefully and cook as the brown sugar caramelizes and blends with the flour.
When just browned on both sides, remove to a hot platter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste and serve.
Bacon strips make a nice garnish for this dish.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cook hot dogs. Allow to cool. Slit hot dogs within 1/2-inch of ends. Insert 3 strips of cheese.
Wrap in separated triangles of dough.
Keep cheese side up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Saute onion in skillet until onion becomes clear.
Add lean ground meat or chili meat, salt, pepper, garlic powder and red pepper.
Cook until meat is done.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Mix everything in rice cooker; cook.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 in. pan.
Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, milk and vanilla and pour over melted margarine.

title: carameled chex mix
directions: In small microwave bowl, mix butter, Karo, vanilla and brown sugar.
Bring to boil, then pour over dry mixture.
Return entire mixture to microwave.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir, then return to microwave for 2 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: monkey bread(breakfast or snack)
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Place cinnamon and white sugar in a large plastic bag and mix.
Add a few biscuits at a time
and shake to coat, then place in a
greased
tube
pan, layering with pecans and raisins until all
are
used.
Bring brown
sugar and margarine to a boil in
saucepan.
Pour
over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow
to
bake
15 minutes, then turn pan upside down.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix.
Spread over rolls.
Top with small amounts of vegetables of your choice:
shredded carrots, chopped tomatoes, chopped broccoli, chopped celery, chopped cauliflower, chopped green onions. , Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Press down lightly.
Refrigerate up to several hours.
Cut with pizza cutter into wedges.
(Easier to cut before adding vegetables.)
Rolls may be placed on cookie sheet and cut into bars.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Take can of blueberry fruit; pour out juice (set aside).
Add enough water to juice to make about 3 cups.
Put on the stove; let come to a boil.
Add cherry jello to juice and water.
Drain pineapple.
Add pineapple and blueberries to the first mixture. Put in refrigerator to chill.
Take sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and nuts.
Using mixer, mix together.
Put in refrigerator until jello chills.
Pour on top and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Place in large pot and cover with water.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender. Water will cook down, add milk and butter to your pleasure.

title: spicy ham roll-ups with mustard sauce
directions: Mix cream cheese, ham, chilies and olives together; spread on tortillas.
Roll up and place on a cookie sheet.
Cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Cut into 3/4 or 1-inch slices.
Serve with salsa or the spicy Mustard Sauce that follows.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mixture together. Pour 1/2 of batter into a Bundt pan. Mix 3/4 cup brown sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon together and sprinkle over batter in pan. Pour remaining batter into the pan and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot pepper salad
directions: Drain all but pepper salad.
Mix together.
Sprinkle oregano to taste.
Best if let sit for a couple of days before using.
Add diced pepperoni before serving (optional).

title: fabulous chocolate truffles
directions: In a large glass bowl, combine cream and 10 ounces chocolate. Heat in microwave oven on High for 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth and melted.
Stir in butter until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Using a 1 1/4-inch scoop or tablespoon, scrape up mixture into 20 (1 1/2-inch) balls. Place them on wax paper-lined baking pans and freeze 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Make a well in center of mixture. Add yeast mixture, oil and buttermilk.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: corn stuffed pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, saute celery and onion in Crisco until tender; stir in bread crumbs, corn, sage, salt and pepper.
Place half the pork chops on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Spread evenly with stuffing; use about 2/3 cup for each.
Top with remaining chops.
Cover pan with foil; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes more or until meat is tender.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: dietetic applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.
Mix butter, Sucaryl or Sweet*10 and egg until light and fluffy.
Then add flour mixture and applesauce alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in raisins and cereal.
Drop by level teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 48 cookies. Keeps better if refrigerated.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. In another bowl mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip. Then combine the two. Layer with 1/3 cookies. Layer pudding, cookies, pudding, etc., ending with cookies. Chill for a couple of hours.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine other ingredients and stir into flour mixture.
Dip onion rings into batter a few at a time.
Fry in hot oil (about 2 inches deep).
Drain on paper towel and salt to taste.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread and sugar.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs, milk, cinnamon, salt and vanilla until foamy.
Pour over bread and sugar; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir in all remaining ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until firm.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in the bottom of a crock-pot.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a saucepan and heat until smooth.
Pour over the chicken breasts.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: beef 'n' biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and peppers in a large frying pan; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; pull each apart into 2 layers.
Press 10 biscuits in layers over bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese (reserve remaining cheese for topping), sour cream and egg. Mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuit layers on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: rice, hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch glass cake pan with canned tomatoes.
Add a layer of shredded cabbage over tomatoes.
Next, add a layer of uncooked rice and another layer of shredded cabbage.
Next, add a layer of hamburger, sliced onions and bell pepper.
Complete layering process with all ingredients to top of pan.
Pour 1 quart canned tomatoes over all.
Bake one hour at 375°.

title: grandma's oatmeal crisps
directions: In bowl of electric mixer blend shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together oats, flour, coconut, pecans, salt and baking soda.
Stir into beaten mixture, blending well.
Divide dough into four portions, rolling each portion into a log on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until chilled through.
Unwrap and slice.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pig-pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 3 layer round pans at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: easy peppermint brownies
directions: Beat eggs with a wire whisk in a large bowl. Add sugar and stir well. Combine flour and cocoa. Add to egg mixture. Stir in 1 cup butter and flavorings. Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack. Spread Mint Cream Frosting over brownie layer; freeze 15 minutes. Melt chocolate squares and 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Spread over frosting with a pastry brush. Chill until firm; cut into squares. Store in refrigerator. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: pumpkin drop cookies(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Mix well.
Add rolled oats (uncooked), coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen small cookies.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa and milk exactly 1 minute.
Remove and stir in oats and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: italian sauce
directions: Cook 8 hours, then add meatballs.

title: punch
directions: Make tea with hot water and tea bags.
Add cloves, cinnamon and sugar.
When mixture cools, add orange and lemon juice.
Serve hot or cold as desired.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package.
Drain and squeeze to remove moisture.
Combine remaining ingredients and add spinach. Melt 1/4 cup margarine in pan.
Spoon mixture into pan and brown on each side.

title: "fun to make" green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in gallon-size container.
Careful! It will bubble over if you mix it too fast.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple partially.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a 2 quart buttered casserole for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: martha washington cake
directions: Cover raisins and 1/2 cup brown sugar with boiling water and boil down on the stove.
Cream 2 cups brown sugar, lard (or butter, margarine or shortening), eggs, spices, baking powder, milk and baking soda together.
Pour the boiling raisins over this and then add some flour to make dough.
Bake at 350°.
This will also make a nice fruit cake by adding mixed fruit, nuts, dates and figs.

title: onion soup
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender.
Pour in saucepan.
Add chicken broth.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thick, add 1 can Pet milk and cook until thick.
Line serving bowl with grated Swiss cheese.
Pour soup into bowl.

title: loose cabbage roll
directions: Saute meat, onion, green pepper and celery until meat is browned.
Remove from heat.
Add rice, salt and pepper.
In casserole, place layers of meat and cabbage.
Pour juice over. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: gluten roast
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add all at once to 2 cups water. Stir quickly with a whisk.
Form into a roll.
Place in glass loaf pan.
Cover with vegetable broth or tomato juice.
Scatter 3 bay leaves on top.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: peanut sauce with mutton
directions: Cut mutton into small pieces.
Wash in salted water.
Add salt and a little white pepper.
Steam for 15 minutes.
Grind together onion, tomatoes and peppers.
Add to mixture the water, okra and eggplant.
Boil 7 minutes.
Grind peanuts to a paste.
Add 2 tablespoons cold water; stir into soup.
Add salt and allow to simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: spicy chicken wings(soul food)
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle with cayenne and paprika. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Remove from refrigerator and brown chicken wings well in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Remove wings.
Cook onions in fat until limp.
(Drain off fat, if desired.)
Stir in soup and water.
Add wings.
Cover and cook 15 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add green peppers and cook 15 minutes longer or until wings are done. Serve with hot rice.

title: poor man pizza
directions: Put ketchup on bread.
Top onion and pepper on ketchup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, or golden brown and cheese melts.
Makes 1 serving.
Make as many as you like.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Cool completely. Add 1 large Cool Whip.
Serve with fruit: strawberries, bananas, kiwi fruit, apples, pineapples or peaches.

title: coffee cake squares
directions: Cream together the margarine and the sugar until light and fluffy.
Separate the eggs and then beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add the lemon flavoring and egg yolks to the sugar and margarine mixture.
Add flour and beat in.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Note:
The dough will be stiff.

title: baking mix(bisquick)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Use with any biscuit recipe.
Yields approximately 11 cups.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in a small saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve completely.
Remove from heat and stir in pineapple; set aside to cool.
Combine Eagle Brand and cream cheese, blending until smooth.
Stir in jello mixture and baby food.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9-cup mold and chill until firm or can be put in a bowl.
Will keep well in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip squares(microwave)
directions: Cream margarine and vanilla in bowl.
Add brown sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add egg and beat thoroughly. Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in half of chocolate pieces.
Turn into an ungreased 1 1/2 quart glass dish.
Top with remaining chocolate pieces.
Cook, uncovered, 7 to 8 minutes on Medium High.
Rotate dish 1 quarter turn once.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix these thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of Christian living.

title: semi-yankee pot roast
directions: Spray
electric
skillet
with Pam.
Brown roast on all sides, being
careful to cook off all fat.
Add 1 quart water, onion soup and Kitchen Bouquet.
Simmer until meat is tender. Surround
meat with potatoes, carrots and onions, basting with meat juices.
When vegetables
are
done remove and add cornstarch dissolved	in 1/2 cup water to liquid in skillet.
Stir constantly until gravy boils.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add bananas and chopped pecans.
Pour half of mixture into 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan and hold in refrigerator until firm.
Jell remaining half only to thick pouring consistency. Spread sour cream on first mixture and pour remaining half on top. Place in refrigerator to jell entire mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: amish church cookies
directions: Add a little more flour if they are too flat.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower mix
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Save 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Put bacon on paper towel to help drain excess grease. Break broccoli and cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Place in large bowl.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Pour over vegetables.
Add cheese and mix all together.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.
Delicious.

title: ralph's "company's coming" chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Add garlic to oil and saute breasts until golden brown.
Pour vinegar and wine over chicken.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7-Up, cornstarch, sugar and Jell-O until thick.
Cool. Place strawberries in baked pie shell and Jell-O mixture over them.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread out rolls on a cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread over crust.
Top with your choice of fresh vegetables: broccoli, cauliflower, green peppers, tomatoes, onions, olives, mushrooms, radishes, celery, cheese, etc.
Cover with plastic wrap and push vegetables into cheese mixture.
Let set overnight in refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn with air popper.
Mix first 4 ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 4 minutes over medium heat. Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and pour over popcorn.
Mix well and place in disposable aluminum turkey roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt and mix.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Bake at 325°.

title: coconut pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, beat pumpkin, oil, eggs and yolk until smooth. Add pie filling and beat 1 minute.
Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: larry's egg rolls
directions: Finely chop vegetables.
Brown ground beef and crumble finely. Lightly stir-fry veggies.
Mix meat and veggies in bowl.
Place mixture in wrappers (egg roll).
Cook until lightly browned in Dutch oven on high or in deep fryer.

title: good bread
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Cut gashes and brush with mixture of ingredients listed.
Stuff Swiss cheese between gashes and spread the rest of the butter over top and inside.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan; heat to boiling point.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Cool to room temperature. When cool, stir in cottage cheese, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: snowcap cookies
directions: In heavy pan over low heat, melt chocolate and butter.
Beat eggs and add a little at a time, beating after each addition. Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on oiled cookie sheet, leaving enough space between each to allow them to spread.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and 2 tablespoons sugar in large bowl and heat in microwave for 3 minutes. Stir until blended, then add jello and stir until dissolved. Cool. Add buttermilk and stir to blend. In mixing bowl, beat evaporated milk until peaks form, then add 2 tablespoons sugar. Fold this into the first mixture and add pecans. Pour into a prepared dish.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Mix noodle soup with water as directed.
Maybe a little less water, as you need a batter.
Dip each pork chop into batter and brown lightly.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until not quite soft, just enough that it is thawed and good and warm.
Cut the butter into nice size pieces. Put about 6 slices in the bottom of your casserole dish, then put a layer of broccoli, then a layer of cheese, then a layer of Ritz crackers.
Continue until you have used all ingredients, making sure you have a layer of Ritz crackers on top.
When finished, add milk.
Bake casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee nut bars
directions: Mix well, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside. In large bowl, cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Alternately stir in flour mixture and coffee.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave lemon squares
directions: In 1-cup glass measure, melt butter on High for 45 seconds. In 8-inch square baking dish, mix butter, 1 cup flour, salt and powdered sugar.
Press evenly into bottom.
Cook on Medium-high for 3 to 5 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through, until mixture is bubbly on top.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion in oil in large skillet or Dutch oven. Add tomato sauce, wine and seasonings. Cover. Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain. Add to sauce along with 1/2 cup of the grated cheese. Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight or can be prepared in the morning to serve that night. Before baking, sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of cheese over casserole. Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Wash okra and drain.
Remove tips and stem ends.
Cut okra crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
Combine egg substitute and buttermilk.
Stir in okra and let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine corn meal and next 2 ingredients in a zip top plastic bag.
Drain okra, small portion at a time.
Spray baking sheet with cooking spray.
Place okra on baking sheet and sprinkle canola oil over the okra.
Bake at 375° to 400° until brown.

title: creamy marinated carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; cut into 1 x 1/4-inch sticks.
Cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Place in shallow container; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour over carrots; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill; stir occasionally. Yields 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Trim and flour meat.
Brown in Dutch oven with hot oil.
Cover with 3 cups water and cook over medium heat for 1 hour or until tender.
Add chopped onion and celery and cook for 30 minutes. Add potatoes and carrots and cook for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, Veg-All and corn.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.

title: mama's old-fashioned coconut pound cake
directions: Defrost coconut.
Eggs and butter should be room temperature.

title: chili-chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain in a large skillet.
Cook and stir onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, pimiento and chili peppers.
In a greased 4-quart casserole, layer half of the noodles and half the chicken. Season with salt and pepper.
Top with half the soup mixture and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add jello, mayonnaise, cheese, pecans and milk, stirring well.
Pour in Pyrex or glass square container.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let congeal overnight or several hours.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: broiled potatoes
directions: Melt butter and mix with basil and salt.
Arrange potatoes on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Brush with oil.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 10 minutes.
Brush with butter mixture and broil 5 minutes moore or until lightly brown and tender.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Skin fryer and remove all visible fat.
Cook until tender in water to cover with 1 teaspoon salt, 1 stalk celery and 1 small onion.
Remove from bone in bite size pieces and place in bottom of large slow cooker.

title: chocolate chocolate chunks
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the flour and baking soda; set aside.
In another large bowl, with an electric mixer, cream together the butter and sugars; add the vanilla and mix well.
Add the cocoa and beat until well blended. Add the cream and, on low speed, gradually add the flour mixture; beat until mixed.
Stir in the chocolate chunks and nuts, if using.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour all ingredients into blender or bowl of electric mixer.
Mix at high speed 15 seconds.
Half-fill well buttered muffin tins (preferably Teflon).
Bake 20 minutes; turn down to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.
Serve at once. Makes 12.

title: cheery cherry cookies
directions: Scald milk and let cool.
In large bowl, mix dry ingredients. Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to cooled milk, then add to flour mixture.
Stir until well blended and forms a soft dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, roll out dough and cut in triangle pieces.
Put one heaping teaspoon of pie filling in center of triangle and bring 3 corners over center.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Put icing on top, if desired.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Serve over shredded cabbage. Yield: 6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and vanilla and stir to make a thick batter.
Melt butter in preheated oven at 325° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take out and pour batter over butter.
Do not stir!
Pour fruit over batter.
Do not stir!
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until crust covers fruit and is golden brown.

title: quick bubble nut bread
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of well-greased loaf or Bundt pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters; roll or shake pieces in mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter; pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool bread in pan 10 minutes, then invert onto serving dish.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to pkg. directions. In a mixing bowl, beat margarine, sugar, and flour on medium speed until blended; add eggs, buttermilk, and vanilla. Beat well and pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, shielding edges with foil after 10 minutes to prevent excessive browning.

title: carol's turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Bake in casserole at 350° until brown and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: You will also need 4 dessert plates, an ice cream scoop and a tablespoon.

title: black-eyed pea supper
directions: Cook sausage in large pan; drain.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings, stir well.
Pour in black-eyed peas with liquid from can.
Cover and simmer slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressing.
Moisten with dressing.
Serve on lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Drain meat and add sauce; cook noodles.
Toss cheese and noodles.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, spoon sauce to cover bottom and then layer noodles, sauce, noodles.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into small balls about the size of a quarter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Mix top 3 ingredients.
(Add a couple drops of yellow food coloring.)
Pour in pie crust and chill.
Serve.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl.
Beat slowly with mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes 4 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme with a mixer until smooth.
A small amount of fruit juice or fruit flavored liqueur may be added for more flavor.
Good with strawberries, bananas, apples, pears, pineapple and kiwi.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in margarine, then stir in cheese, soup and water.
Simmer until well blended.
Fold in rice and broccoli.
Pour into covered glass dish.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: tropical fruit pie
directions: Slice 4 bananas into pie crusts.
Mix pineapple juice, jello, sugar and beaten eggs.
Bring to a full boil.
Take off fire to cool.
Add can of crushed pineapple.
Pour mixture over bananas. Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Pour drained vegetables into casserole dish.
Put in other ingredients.
Mix together. Take one package Ritz crackers (crumbled) and one stick margarine (melted).
Mix together and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fig conserve
directions: Wash figs and cut into small pieces.
Wash oranges.
Squeeze juice into figs.
Grind raisins and oranges, including peeling (using fine plate), and add to figs.
Cook mixture for approximately 55 minutes, until transparent or done.
Stir often to prevent scorching.
Add coarsely chopped pecans to cooked mixture and continue cooking another 5 to 10 minutes, again stirring to keep mixture from scorching.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 8 pints.

title: zucchini and green rice
directions: Slice zucchini in 1/4-inch rounds.
Steam until done, but still firm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rice with lemon juice, parsley and seasonings.
Grease a 3-quart casserole with oil; make a layer each of rice mixture, cottage cheese and zucchini.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: san antonio skillet supper
directions: Cut sausage in half lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut vegetables up; mix all ingredients.
Let set aside at least 1 hour in refrigerator before serving.
Best if let set overnight.

title: spinach enchiladas
directions: Combine broth, peppers, tomatoes, onion and garlic in a 2-quart saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon in heavy skillet until brown; remove from skillet. Saute onion and pepper in bacon fat; add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: artichoke veggie casserole
directions: Dice artichoke hearts (medium) and garlic (fine).
Grate Parmesan and
Mozzarella cheeses.
Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake, covered, in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in small cubes and cook until tender.
Drain potatoes.
Add eggs, relish, mustard, sandwich spread and salad dressing.
Mix well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to a boil. Add peanuts and cook over slow heat until peanuts start cracking.
Let crack for a few minutes, then take off heat and stir in soda.
Pour on a buttered board. When it cools, flip over and let stand for a few minutes. Crack into pieces that you desire.

title: fireman's ceviche(i like this one!)
directions: Mix all the ingredients to marinated fish.
It will only take a couple of peppers and tomatoes.
Add all the other ingredients according to your taste.
Chill and serve.

title: minestrone
directions: This is a fast soup, that is, it takes 10 minutes to get everything into the pot.
It's the prototype for any quick soup. Just start with stock and add any vegetables, potatoes, rice, lentils or other grains or legumes and cook for 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix with Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add pineapple with juice, nuts and marshmallows.
Let chill for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Great as salad or dessert.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with bell pepper and onion; drain.
In skillet, soften tortillas with 1 teaspoon of oil.
Roll ground beef in corn tortillas.
Place in non-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: persian style lima beans
directions: Simmer	onions	in
olive
oil until golden; add cooked limas, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook 25 minutes covered over moderate heat.
Serve cold (room temperature).
Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mash Oreo cookies in blender.
Mix together cookies and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Freeze.
Later, soften ice cream and spread over the Oreo crust.
Spread on top of ice cream the syrup.
Spread on top of syrup a large carton of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the top with more crushed cookies and nuts. Serves 12.

title: spanish cakes
directions: Sift plain all-purpose flour into bowl.
Make hole in flour and mix with hand as biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375°.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add Velveeta and flour to creamed mixture.
Pour apples into casserole dish and top evenly with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: apricot cream cheese delight
directions: Combine jello and pineapple in saucepan.
Heat until mixture simmers.
Add sugar, baby food and cut up cream cheese.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Add Cool Whip, slowly.
Blend in, but do not beat.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan or whatever dish you prefer.
Cover with chopped nuts and chill.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Mix 1 cup cherry juice, 1/2 cup pineapple juice and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boil and add to Jell-O and dissolve.
Add cherries, pineapple and Cola slowly.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add nuts and cream cheese; chill.

title: fiesta funnel cakes
directions: Combine the flour, corn meal, picante sauce, milk, and egg in the bowl of a food processor, fitted with the steel blade. Process until smooth.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 375 degrees.
Oil should be at least 1/2 inch deep.
Cover the bottom opening of a funnel with your finger.
Pour about 1/4 cup of the batter into the funnel. Hold the funnel over the skillet. Remove your finger and move the funnel in a slow, circular motion to form a spiral.
Fry each funnel cake about 1 minute or until edges are golden brown.
Turn the funnel cake over and fry the other side until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper. Immediately sprinkle each funnel cake with 1/4 cup of the cheese.
Serve while still warm and crispy.
Makes about 6 funnel cakes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and cherry juice in saucepan. Cook until it begins to boil.
Stir constantly.
Add drained cherries and continue cooking until the desired thickness is reached.
Remove from heat and add butter and red coloring.
Cool. Pour into pastry lined open dish and add top crust or strips of pastry.
Bake at 450° for ten minutes, then reduce temperature to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cupcake cones(for parties)
directions: Mix
ingredients together well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 24 flat bottom ice cream cones, filling 3/4
full.	Place
upright on cookie sheet.
Frost to your choice. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch inch pan. Layer beans over meat.
Layer tortillas over beans.
Layer grated cheese over tortillas.
Layer Ro-Tel over cheese.
Mix soup together and cover the top of the casserole.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave foil on casserole for 10 minutes before serving.

title: double treat cookies
directions: Mix all together; form into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar; flatten on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375°.
Makes about 35 cookies.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat 4 minutes on both sides.
Do not overcook or they will be dry.
Transfer to serving platter.
Add chives or green onion, lime or lemon juice, brandy, parsley and mustard to frying pan.
Cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth until sauce is smooth.
Stir in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: hanky panks
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; drain.
On low heat, add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese melts.
Spread on party rye or pumpernickel bread.
To serve, place under broiler until bubbly. These freeze well.

title: chicken curry
directions: In large frypan, melt butter on medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in curry powder.
Turn heat to simmer and stir in soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or until done.
Serve over rice.

title: sour cream roll out cookies
directions: In a large bowl, place sugar, salt, soda, flour and shortening.
Mix with hands, rolling shortening and flour-sugar mixture together until crumbly (looks like purchased pie crust mix).
Add egg and part of sour cream.
Cut liquid into flour with a knife and add remaining sour cream.
Dough will be soft.
You can now choose to add either vanilla, anise, brandy, rum, etc. Divide dough into parts.
Chill overnight.
Flour board and roll out for cutters.
Can be rolled more than once.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 stick melted butter and cheese.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust until almost done. Combine sugar, margarine and cornstarch and put in pan over medium heat until margarine has melted, then add 2 1/4 cups milk and bring to a full boil. Put in pie crust and bake 10 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle top of pie with cinnamon and cool.

title: polka daters
directions: Mix dates and hot water, let cool.
Beat margarine, sugar and eggs together until creamy.
Sift flour and baking soda together and stir in.
Stir in date mixture, vanilla flavoring and chocolate morsels, mixing well.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Top with chocolate morsels and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Wrap sweet potatoes in aluminum foil; prick several times with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft. Chill thoroughly.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Combine potato, pepper, green onion and parsley in a bowl; toss gently.
Combine vinegar, honey, water, oil, salt and oregano in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously to blend.

title: spinach with pine nuts
