directions: Wash spinach and let dry.
Heat oil in large saute pan over medium-low heat. Add garlic and saute about 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Raise heat to medium-high.
Add spinach and salt. Saute, turning spinach with tongs for 25 seconds, until spinach just wilts. Reduce heat. Add pine nuts. Drizzle lemon juice and season with pepper.

title: fettucini primavera
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In skillet, cook, on medium heat, broccoli, zucchini, green peppers, onion and basil in butter, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and mushrooms.
Toss vegetables with noodles.
Serve with cheese, if desired.
Makes 5 servings.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Fill baking dish in order given; salt and pepper each layer. Bake in slow oven in covered dish 1 hour.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain salmon well.
Bone and flake.
Combine everything except parsley and nuts.
Chill several hours.
Roll into log (wax paper helps).
Roll log in nuts and parsley.
Serve with party rye bread or party crackers (Town House).
Keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Mix in sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Remove from pan immediately.
Yield 36.
Carbohydrate 21 g, protein 3 g, fat 10 g, calories 186.
One serving = 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange, 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: bawatsa(appetizer)
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Drain well.
Spread dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread meat mixture on dough. Layer pepperoni, onions and green pepper on meat.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll from short end, making sure ends of dough are secure. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Slice and serve hot.

title: smoked sausage, vegetables and mexican rice
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Add rice; brown until rice is golden brown.
Add garlic and onion; saute 1 to 2 minutes. Add tomato sauce, water, cumin, salt and pepper.
Add sausage and carrots.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Cover; simmer another 10 minutes, or until the liquid is evaporated and the rice is soft.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Combine flour, oleo and pecans and press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Beat until smooth the cream cheese, sugar and add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Combine pudding with milk and pour over cheese layer.
Spread a thin layer of Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with crushed pecans. Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: chinese barbecue pork
directions: Combine soy sauce, red wine, cinnamon, honey, garlic, food coloring and brown sugar in a low flat dish. Lay 2 pork tenderloins in marinade. Let sit for 1 hour at room temperature, rotating tenderloins several times. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and test for doneness. Let cool and slice. Use Chinese hot mustard and sesame seeds for dipping.

title: southern eggs
directions: Brown sausage and drain well, cube the bread slices.
Spray dish with Pam.
Layer 9 x 13-inch glass dish as follows:
1st layer - sausage, 2nd layer - bread cubes, 3rd layer - cheese.
Mix the eggs and milk, season to taste and pour over the layered mixture. Cover tightly and let sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: quick microwave bean dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, beans and cheese in microwave dish.
Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes uncovered until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chili cheese nachos
directions: Prepare chili according to directions on mix.
Microwave chili and cheese on High for 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Layer half of chips, half of chili mixture. Then layer other half of chips and chili mixture on large serving platter.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers in 1/4-inch slices.
Peel and slice onions real thin.
Place cucumbers and onions in glass or enamel bowl.
Cover with a brine made of salt and water.
Drain and rinse thoroughly under running water.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in preserving kettle and bring to boil over high heat. Add cucumbers and onions.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Pack in hot sterilized jars to within 1/8-inch of top and seal.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the flours, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the egg white, whole eggs, oil, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat the mixture with an electric mixer on high speed until fluffy.
Stir in the flour mixture until it is just moistened.
Stir in the rhubarb and walnuts.
Divide the batter between 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 50 minutes or until a pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Set the pans on a rack for 10 minutes, then turn out the loaves to cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: stuffed date drops
directions: Cut nuts in half lengthwise.
Stuff in dates.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat brown sugar and shortening on medium until well combined.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Gently stir in stuffed dates.
Drop 1 date per cookie on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden.
Remove to rack to cool.
Frost with Golden Frosting.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat until mixed well. Especially good for barbecue wieners.

title: jumer's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast with warm water; set aside.
Melt butter; set aside.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix cold water and biscuit mix.
Add yeast mixture; let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Divide dough into 4 sections.
Roll each into 4 x 12-inch section on a floured board.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll into long tube.
Cut into 1-inch pieces; place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining sections.
Brush remaining melted butter on top of rolls; sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: malai seekh
directions: Combine garlic, ginger, green chili paste, black pepper and salt with the chicken.
Add about 1/4 cup water, and lightly boil chicken until cooked through.
Let cool then finely shred with fingers.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage for 6 to 8 minutes.
Season to taste.
Saute bread crumbs in butter until brown and crisp.
Layer cabbage, white sauce and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine the pudding mix, sugar and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until the mixture comes to a full boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Stir in the sour cream, blending well.
Pour into a bowl or dessert dishes.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soda pop ice cream
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Mix all together.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
the
following
ingredients well:	oil, sugar, hot water and egg yolks.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, carrots and nuts. Fold in 4 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Grease and flour cake mold. Pour in mold.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Add walnuts, pineapple and grapes.
Pour into a 6 cup mold and chill overnight.
Serves 16.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, 1 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla for 20 minutes.
Spread on base.
Slice bananas; spread with crushed pineapple.
Spread whipped topping on top.
Decorate with cherries and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl or container.
Use 1/3 cup of mix to make 1 cup hot chocolate.

title: bud lord's 5 lemon pie(if you can unpucker after 1st bite, you can have 2nd!)
directions: Mix lemon juice, sugar, egg yolks and water.
Heat them. Make a paste of cornstarch and a little water.
Add slowly to lemon mixture, while stirring.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time!
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add 8 tbsp. sugar, a little at a time.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put on hot filling, sealing all edges.
Bake 8 minutes at 400.
Cool.
Do not make pie a day ahead of time!

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients reserving 1/2 cup meat loaf fixings. Press into loaf pan.
Cover with reserved meat loaf seasoning. Bake in 375 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together the ground cranberries, ground oranges and sugar. Let stand for one hour.
Add finely cut apple, some chopped nuts and the prepared jello.
Mix together.
Place in the refrigerator to set.

title: dorethea's french dressing
directions: Set to season at least 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: raisin fudge bars
directions: Melt butter; stir in dry pudding mixes and milk.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Blend in sugar, then stir in vanilla and the raisins.
Pour into a 10 x 10-inch buttered pan.
Chill before cutting.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except hard-boiled eggs and olives.
Place half on bottom of a bread pan or in any pan you are going to bake it in of that size or shape into a loaf.
Place hard boiled eggs in a row in center of loaf and place a row of stuffed olives on each side.
Put rest of meat mixture on top and pat
down or shape loaf and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear and thick.
Add 2 tablespoons of strawberry jello and mix.
Slice fresh strawberries in baked crust.
Pour cornstarch mix over strawberries crust. Serve with whipped cream as topping.

title: quik thai-fried noodles
directions: Crumble noodles.
In skillet use a little oil; brown noodles. Set aside.
In same pan brown sausage; set aside.
In same pan stir-fry vegetables.
Combine all ingredients in pan.
Add seasoning packets from noodles and 1/4 cup water.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes, until noodles are tender.
Serve with soy sauce and rice.

title: low-fat chocolate fudge
directions: Put butter, sugar and milk together.
Stir, stir, stir.
Then add the chocolate chips into this and melt.
Add baby prunes, Marshmallow Creme and walnuts.
Add vanilla to mixture.
Spray spoon with Pam so mixture won't be so sticky.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Mix all together.
Cut eggplant in half.
Cut out the middle and fill with the mixture.
Fry eggplant on both sides, then put in baking dish.
Pour tomatoes on top and bake at 375° until done.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix and heat the liquids until it boils, then cool.
Mix the kraut (squeeze it good) and mix with the rest.
Pour the cooled liquid over.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
The longer it stays, the better it will taste.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks if stored in a glass jar.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; then add eggs.
Next add dry ingredients with molasses and hot water.
Bake in 7 x 10 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients, reserving enough beef to roll ball in. Refrigerate 1 day, then roll in excess beef.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup flour and toss with apples and nuts.
The flour will help suspend them in the cake batter.

title: spiced cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove whole pieces.
Serve warm.
Float lemon slice on top.

title: potato cakes
directions: Press potatoes in a colander to remove as much liquid as possible.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg and onion; now stir in flour, salt, pepper and potatoes.
Press mixture into small hamburgers.
Fry in deep fryer, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: bernice's creamed corn
directions: Combine corn, salt and water.
For fresh corn, cook about 5 minutes.
For frozen corn, heat until it separates.
Add margarine and evaporated milk.
Make a thickening from flour and water, using about 3 tablespoons of flour.
Bring corn to a boil and stir slowly as you add the thickening.

title: on-the-grill fish steaks
directions: Place serving size portions of fish on well-greased grill. Spray grill well before putting on fish.
Baste fish with sauce and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook about 5 inches from hot coals for 8 minutes.
Baste with sauce, then turn and cook for 7 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes or turns shiny white.
Serves 4.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Wash 8 green peppers (or red sweet) and bake in flat pan in 400° oven for about 30 minutes, or until they "color" nicely. Remove from heat and let cool in covered pot to facilitate peeling. Remove stem and try to spoon out the seeds.
Place in serving dish, and pour over a generous amount of olive oil as well as salt and minced garlic.
Good with cooked or broiled meat, especially lamb.

title: slimmed-down apple spice cake
directions: Note:
Sugar substitute can be used for up to half of the sugar.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all the ingredients except crackers and cheese in a casserole dish.
Put on top of crushed Ritz.
Add cheese.
Then add the other half of Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish and put blueberries on top of melted butter. Mix sugar, milk and flour. Pour on blueberries. Bake at 350° until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Cool cake, split layers to make 4 layers.
Mix Jell-O, add strawberries and add strawberry jell pie mix.
Mix and let stand until jelled.
Mix vanilla pudding and let stand until firm.
Place 1/2 of layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Place on top of cake layer 1/4 of vanilla pudding, 1/4 of Jell-O and 1/4 of Cool Whip or whipped cream. Sprinkle with coconut (optional).
Add 1/2 layer on the mixture and repeat the measurement of ingredients until all cake layers have been used.
Place the last 1/4 of everything on top of last layer and top with coconut, if desired.

title: hot potato salad with bacon
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Do not overcook.
Peel while hot; cut in thin slices.
Fry bacon; add onion.
Saute slowly until onion becomes transparent.
Remove from heat.
Carefully pour combined vinegar and stock or water.
Bring to a boil and pour over potatoes.
Add a couple spoons of sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: party dip
directions: Blend soup into cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in rest of ingredients, chill and serve with crackers or chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and stir in vegetable or olive oil and salad dressing mix.
Cook and cool vegetable medley.
Mix with pasta and refrigerate or add to pasta and heat and serve hot.

title: steve's shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add cream of celery soup and 1/2 can of water and chopped onion and simmer until onion is cooked. Place in casserole dish and cover with mashed potatoes.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and serve.

title: peanut butter hardtack
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
With candy thermometer bring to 300°.
In cast-iron skillet (buttered) add peanut butter.
Add hot syrup and stir.
Put on buttered cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cake mix, butter and pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top, then pour butter on top of mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top of butter and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add molasses and egg; mix well. Slowly add flour and spice mixture. Stir in raisins and walnuts. Roll into balls; roll in sugar and press. Bake at 350 degrees 8-10 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs and add to oleo.
Then add sugar, flour, salt and milk; mix well.
Add coconut and pineapple.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown steak with onion.
Add catsup and water, more depending on amount of gravy you want.
Simmer.
The longer the better. Great when served with boiled potatoes.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients, except raisins, with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, greased.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen; remove from pan.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: turtle cake
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour half into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

While batter is baking, melt caramels in margarine and evaporated milk, using double boiler. Remove cake from oven; pour caramel mixture over baked layer. Scatter over that mixture of pecan pieces and chocolate chips. Pour rest of batter over all.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: saucy sausage surprise(sounds "awful" but it is great!)
directions: Combine cranberry sauce and mustard.
Mix well.
Pour into crock-pot. Add small sausages and cook on low 2 hours or you can keep them warm until ready to serve.
Provide colored toothpicks and lots of different kinds of crackers to serve with sausages. You can serve cheese wedges also.

title: microwave honey-mustard sauce
directions: In a 2-cup glass measuring cup or bowl combine all ingredients.
Cook in microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until butter is melted and all ingredients are blended.
Stir halfway through.
Brush onto chicken while barbecuing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kay's chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick and then cool.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup white sugar until stiff and fold in with the pumpkin mixture.
Put in a baked pie shell and refrigerate the day before.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain and cool.
Place in bottom of a buttered, 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and lemon juice.
Mix together in separate bowl dry ingredients. Then combine with first mixture. Now stir in morsels and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: judy o's "no cooking" spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook the pasta to the al dente stage.
Drain cooked pasta but leave quite moistened.
While hot, add first 5 ingredients.
While tossing to melt the Mozzarella, sprinkle the grated cheese.
Serve immediately with pepper mill for guests.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in 2 1/2 quarts water.
Cook beans in same water until tender.
Add sugar, syrup and ketchup and continue cooking for approximately 1/2 hour.
Add uncooked bacon cut in half strips.
Bake at 325° for approximately 4 to 5 hours until most of liquid is absorbed.

title: super play doh
directions: Mix together.
Add 3 tablespoons oil and 2 cups boiling water. Stir and knead.
Cool.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together. Shape into one large loaf or divide into two standard loaf pans. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Pour Basting Sauce over loaf and bake 30 minutes more or until done.

title: chocolate mallow microwave cake
directions: Place all ingredients, except marshmallows and frosting, in mixing bowl.
Blend at lowest speed.
Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in an 8-inch square dish.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes, if needed to finish cooking. Immediately place marshmallows on cake.
Let stand a couple of minutes to partially melt.
Spread with frosting.

title: spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer cake pans.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices together.

Beat shortening, sugar and eggs on high speed of electric mixer about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture alternately with the sour cream at low speed, beginning and ending with flour. Scrape bowl frequently.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 25 to 30 minutes for the layers or until the cake tests done.
Make the Filling for the middle of the cake, then frost the cake with Frosting.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Oil shells lightly.
Put into 375° oven until crisp.
Layer in single layer on 2 cookie sheets.
Mash beans.
Put in hot skillet with 1 tablespoon oil and reserved juice.
Fry until juice is absorbed (3 to 5minutes).
Layer while hot onto shells.
Spread with taco sauce.
Sprinkle on corn and cheese.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes until cheese is melted and lightly brown.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix as for any cake, adding rhubarb and nuts last.
Top before baking with additional 1/3 cup brown sugar mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve slightly warm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: orange-glazed pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a medium bowl.
Combine egg, oil, pumpkin and milk.
Make a well in flour mixture.
Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Stir just to blend.
Spoon batter into 12 buttered muffin cups and place 1 teaspoon marmalade on each.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: savory beef
directions: Brown
onions
slowly
in
fat.
Add meat to onions and brown. Mix
flour
and dry seasonings and sprinkle over meat. Add stock, vinegar and ketchup.
Cover tightly.
Simmer until meat
is tender, 1 1/2 hours approximately.
Serve in ring of mashed potatoes or rice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip potatoes and add sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar and flour; add butter and mix all together with fork.
Add nuts and mix.
Place topping over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash cakes
directions: Grate squash and onion.
Add egg, salt and pepper.
Add corn meal a
little
at a time until mixture is dry.
Spoon in small amounts
into a 375° electric skillet with 1/2 inch oil. Brown on both
sides,
turning
only
once.
Will be crunchy. Serve hot as a vegetable.

title: cheddar shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased loaf pan, 7 x 12-inch.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Blend the pumpkin, evaporated milk, brown sugar, nutmeg, cloves, ginger, salt, eggs, sugar and cinnamon and turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix and nuts on top.
Drizzle with the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cut into squares and use Cool Whip on top.

title: apple delight
directions: Wash apple. Cut into 8 wedges. Wrap each apple wedge in a crescent roll pieces. Place in a baking dish. Melt butter. Pour over apple. Next, pour Mountain Dew over. Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: batter bread
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar, salt and margarine (cool).
Pour warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast, stir until dissolved, add to milk mix.
Stir in flour, batter will be stiff.
Beat until blended, about 2 minutes.
Cover and let rise until double (40 minutes).
Stir down and beat for 1/2 minute.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato juice.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350°, covered, with tomato juice poured over top of balls.
Turn after 1/2 hour.
Cook for 1 hour total.

title: southern pig picking cake
directions: Follow cake directions on box.
Add other ingredients.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Bake in 3 layer pans in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: black forest pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip on bottom of pie crust. Combine milk and pudding mix in medium bowl. Blend with wire whisk or electric mixer (low speed) for 1 minute. Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over Cool Whip that's in crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over that leaving a 1-inch border and forming a depression in center of Cool Whip.
Spoon cherry pie filling in center. Chill three hours.
Garnish with melted chocolate, if desired.

title: rio grande chili
directions: Peel and chop onion.
Melt butter in the frying pan over low heat.
Add onion and saute until soft and golden.
Add the meat and stir until browned.
Put meat mixture in a large saucepan and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until sauce has become thick, about one hour.
Stir often.

title: cornbread - never fail
directions: Mix well.
Pour in hot, greased muffin tins or cornbread stick pans.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except baking soda and popped corn, in saucepan; heat until boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir well.
It will be light and foamy.
Add popcorn.
Toss and coat well.
Pour on cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 175° to 200°, stirring occasionally.
Remove and break apart. Store in airtight containers.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Set aside.
In saucepan, blend flour, milk and vanilla.
Heat and stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir until cooler.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Beat until fluffy.

title: frosty mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add measured liquid. Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened.

title: waldorf chicken sandwich
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Serve on bread and lettuce leaf.

title: apple bar cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add flour and other ingredients.
Add the apples last.
Mix well and place in a greased pan, 9 x 13-inch, and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Cut in bars when cool.
Yields about 20 bars.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in jar and use by spoonfuls in a cup of hot water as desired.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each piece of chicken between two sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Sprinkle with parsley and 1/4 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Place a ham slice and a cheese slice on each chicken breast; roll up from short side and secure rolls with wooden picks.
Combine mayonnaise and water; brush on chicken, covering all sides. Combine bread crumbs and remaining 3/4 teaspoon Italian seasoning; dredge chicken rolls in mixture.
Place on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove wooden picks.

title: haystacks
directions: In mixing bowl, beat egg well.
Stir in honey, yogurt, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in combined coconut, chocolate, flour and lemon rind.
With a wooden spoon, mix until well combined.
Use an egg cup to form the haystack.
Dip small end of egg cup into cold water to chill.
Firmly press 1 tablespoon coconut mixture into cup.
Slip out onto foil or parchment lined baking sheets.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: diet coffee shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until mixture froths.
For a thicker shake, add more ice cubes.
Can add different extracts for a different taste.

title: beryl's shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with squeeze of lemon until creamy.
Fold in shrimp.
The amount of seasonings to add depends on how zesty you like your dip.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Mix yogurt, French dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper in medium glass or plastic bowl or in heavy plastic bag. Add remaining ingredients; toss until vegetables are evenly coated. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart glass pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture to coat and arrange in a single layer in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Serves 4 to 5.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in greased casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Mix crab or shrimp, sharp cheese, onion and pimento.
Put in pie pan; dot pieces of cream cheese on top.
Combine remaining ingredients until smooth, about 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until a knife comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool a few minutes before serving.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand overnight.
Place in containers and freeze.
Makes approximately 11 cups.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Spray a 10 pie plate with Pam.
In a blender, mix all ingredients, except meat and cheese.
Mix 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate and sprinkle meat of choice and cheese over the top. Lightly stir in.
Any chopped vegetables may be added, such as: celery, onion, bell pepper, broccoli, pimento, zucchini, olives, etc.

title: kart-wheels
directions: Mix flour, margarine, powdered sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts. Shape each into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Make an indentation 1 3/4-inches in diameter and 3/4-inch deep.
Fill indentation with about 2 tablespoons of filling.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is done, bring to a boil the sugar and milk; add the flavoring. Punch holes in cake and pour the milk over it.
When cool, beat the whipping cream and spread over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over cake.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture alternately with the pumpkin.
Transfer to a greased 12 cup fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 60 - 65 minutes. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: relish dip
directions: Dice onions and tomatoes.
Combine with other ingredients. Chill 4 to 5 hours and serve with Doritos.

title: coconut lemon pecan cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix together the eggs and oil. Add to cake mix; beat well.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Set out a shallow 2 quart baking dish and a large saucepan. Rinse and clean out peppers.
Drop peppers into boiling salted water to cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove peppers and drain.

title: crusty sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into casserole dish.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Squeeze excess water from spinach and set aside.
Mix package dressing and sour cream.
Add bacon bits and spinach.
Spread a thin layer on tortilla.
Roll up then slice into 1 - 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Hold pieces together with toothpicks.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and green peppers slowly in shortening until onions are yellow.
Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart. Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings and mix.
Place in 2-quart casserole; cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fantastic dessert
directions: Blend in food processor with metal blade until completely mixed.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: orange blossom cooler punch
directions: Combine frozen concentrates and water.
Place sherbet and ice cream in bottom of large punch bowl.
Break into small pieces with a large spoon.
Add juice mixture until sherbet and ice cream are partially melted.
On top of punch, float "blossoms" of orange slices centered with maraschino cherries.
Makes about 5 quarts or 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Will need a 9 x 13-inch pan (grease bottom only).

title: rhonda's famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together; sugar, brown sugar, eggs, oleo, crisco; then add flour salt baking soda. Beat well then add chocolate chips. (I use small chips) Bake 10-12 minutes at 375°F. The secret is not to over bake.

title: cheezy cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine the cabbage, onion, and water in large saucepan. Cook until cabbage is limp but not mushy (about 5 minutes. Drain. Add Cavender's seasoning, soup, and bacon.
Stir well. Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole. Top with cornbread crumbs. Bake for 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix in heavy 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven the tomatoes, wine, broth, sugar and seasonings.
Stir in beef chunks. Add carrots, celery and onions.
Cover and bake about 3 hours, stirring twice, until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.

title: nana's best brownies
directions: Use 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
In the mixer, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, then chocolate and finally, the flour.
Mix well and spread evenly into ungreased pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in quick oats and chocolate chips.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large pan.
Cover with water.
Cook until chicken is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken from pan.
Refrigerate broth until fat comes to the top.
Discard the fat.
Remove the skin and bones from the chicken breast and discard.
Cube chicken.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add carrots, celery, onions, garlic salt, bay leaves, salt, pepper, parsley and chicken.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add noodles.
Cook 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
This freezes well.
If soup is too thick, add additional canned chicken broth.
Add additional salt, if desired.
This recipe can be halved if you do not want to freeze.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, melt butter and saute onions until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Stir in chili powder and garlic powder.
Blend in rice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove lid and sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Cover until melted.
Serve.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mix, another layer of crackers and rest of pudding mix.
Layer crackers and spread frosting.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: creole black eyed peas
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Fill with water until 3/4 full.
Cover and boil until peas are tender adding water if needed.

title: japanese rice chex
directions: Mix
shoyu, sugar and Tabasco together.
Drizzle liquid on Rice
Chex,
turning
and mixing.
Sprinkle furikake while turning.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.	Mix every 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground turkey; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning with 1/2 cup water.
After cooked, cool down in fridge.
(This is best done ahead.)
Prepare salad out of lettuce, green pepper, tomatoes and onions.
Top with shredded cheese and meat.
Right before serving, mix up with dressing and Fritos.
Serve right away.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease 15 x 1 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; line with wax paper. Grease and flour paper.
Beat eggs and sugar on medium speed.
Add pumpkin, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
On a small towel, sift the 3 tablespoons sugar evenly. Turn cake out on towel; peel wax paper off.
Roll up cake and towel together.
Let cool.

title: rum raisin bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together the sugar, the butter and add the eggs.
Mix well.
Add the milk, nutmeg, and rum; stirring until well combined.
Stir in the bread cubes and raisins.
Let sit for 5 to 10 minutes and stir again.
Pour into a 2 quart baking dish or pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with plain yogurt.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet. Cover bottom with graham crackers.
Cook sugar and oleo. Boil over medium heat 1 minute.
Pour over crackers. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Cook 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Let cool. Cut in squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube Velveeta cheese over top of chicken.
Add 1 cup milk to soup. Stir well and pour over chicken mixture.
Fix Stove Top stuffing according to directions, using the chicken broth as the liquid. Put on top of other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maraschino nut cake
directions: Sift first four ingredients.
Add next four ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add egg whites.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans or a loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with a buttercream frosting.

title: quick rolls
directions: Stir
together
yeast,
flour, powdered milk, honey and salt. Combine
warm
water and butter until butter is melted. Add to yeast
mixture.
Stir in flour.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes. Knead
until the dough does not stick to your hands. Pat out dough to about 1 1/2-inch thickness and cut in 2-inch rounds. Place in
greased
9 x 13-inch pan and let rise 20 to 25 minutes. Bake
at
400° for 10 minutes.
Brush butter over top of rolls.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Drizzle margarine evenly over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You'll have a cake on top of a good pumpkin pie.

title: chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Melt oleo in a large frying pan or wok.
Flour and brown chicken pieces on both sides.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Mix soup and milk and pour over top.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Poke holes in cake.
Pour Kahlua over entire cake.
Cut cake in pieces, then layer in large, flat bottom bowl (clear if possible) with cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bar chips, then repeat all 4 layers.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Line crock-pot with foil, leaving enough to cover the potatoes.
Slice potatoes and onions.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Bake at 400° until tender or done.
Combine tomatoes with cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 or 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: mom elizer's pear honey
directions: Put pears into food chopper (coarse grind).
Makes about 8 cups.
Place pears in large saucepan.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Allow to cook for 35 minutes after it comes to a full boil.
Pack in clean jars.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drop vegetables into boiling water until they separate; drain. Arrange in medium sized greased baking dish.
Microwave or heat in pan the Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and milk.
Mix and pour over vegetables.
Bake 3/4 to 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: pat's snack cake
directions: Mix flour,
sugar
and	pie
spice.
Add
egg, milk and nuts (add
last).
Melt	butter	in 9-inch baking dish.	Pour batter in baking dish with butter.
Bake at 325° until done in center.
Eat hot or cold.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Cover with nuts.
Pour melted margarine over all and bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tomato soup
directions: Wash and cut up tomatoes, onions, celery and put parsley in. Cook until celery
tender. Put through sieve. Add bay leaves. Take a little hot tomato juice out, melt butter in it and add to flour to make a paste.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and carrot until tender.
Melt margarine and saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add flour and then chicken broth and cook until thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add a pinch of nutmeg.
Process all in food processor.
Return to pan and add cheese and half and half.
Add herbs and heat until cheese melts.
If too thick, thin with milk.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Let stand at room temperature.	Blend.	Roll in crushed pecans and parsley flakes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ice cream cone trees
directions: Add the green food coloring to the icing.
Ice the cone.
Put on M&M's and gumdrops for decoration.

title: inspection cookies
directions: Combine Karo and sugar and bring to slight boil.
Add peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Slightly crush Special K and mix with peanut butter mixture.
Press mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips and spread over Special K.
Cut into bars.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook shrimp; remove veins.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic until tender.
Blend in flour, seasonings and tomatoes.
Add shrimp and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook pinto beans in pot on the stove or in a crock-pot (add onion and garlic salt to beans) until done.
Fry hamburger in a skillet (you may add more onion).
Drain hamburger; then add chili mix and mix well.
Add the can of tomato sauce.
It will be sticky. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Then add hamburger mix to the beans and mix well.
You may add salt or garlic salt, if needed.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Add potatoes and shake until covered thoroughly.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning potatoes once or twice.

title: crisscross strudel
directions: Mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Mix together the vanilla and milk; set aside.
Cream together the sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add egg; mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk mixture. Knead with hands just until mixed.
Add more flour if sticky. Grease jelly roll pan lightly; set a small portion of dough aside for topping.
Spread remaining dough in pan, using your hands.
Be sure to cover sides of pan.
Pour filling into pan.
Roll remaining dough; cut into strips.
Place strips across filling, creating a crisscross effect.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: garden goulash
directions: Heat iron skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Add garlic and onion, cook 1 minute.
Add rest of vegetables.
Stir vegetables frequently and saute 5 to 10 minutes until cooked to your liking.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place cheese in bowl.
Let stand at room temperature until soft.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend with low speed of mixer.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Roll into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll into chopped nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add chopped celery,
sliced carrots and tomato juice.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add cabbage,
shredded and diced potatoes.
Cook another 1/2 hour. Serve over noodles.

title: shirley's sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion.
Mix chicken, onion, green chiles, enchilada sauce and 3/4 cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat broth and half and half together.
Dip tortillas and stuff with chicken mixture. Pour broth mixture over enchiladas and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° covered.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugar and milk to boiling.
Let boil 5 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Put in small baking bowl.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Triscuit crackers go real well with this.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Cut butter or margarine into mixture.
Pour can of fruit with liquid into baking dish.
Spoon flour mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown. May serve warm with ice cream.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: eddie's baked rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on the package.
Cut bacon into small strips and fry with the onions, which have been diced, until both the onions and bacon are crisp-tender.
Add to the cooked rice and spread in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious served as a side dish with ham or pork.

title: apple casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Cook chicken (boil or bake).
Combine melted butter and stuffing mix.
Pour in bottom of casserole dish.
Crumble chicken over stuffing.
Blend together cream of celery, cream of chicken and water until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sauce for tuna balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim bread and cut each piece into 5 pieces (65 pieces).
Put on cookie sheet and place in 200° oven for about 20 minutes or until dried out, not brown.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add Coke and cool to jelly point. Add pineapple and marshmallows to the jello mixture and congeal. Mix pineapple juice, one egg yolk and 1 tablespoon cornstarch and heat until thick.
Cool and mix with Cool Whip.
Spread over congealed salt.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Use strawberry jello if available, otherwise use red jello.

title: jordan's blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries; stir in by hand.
Fold in the rest of the berries.
Grease muffin tin well; top surface also.
Pile mixture high in cups and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut molasses custard
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses, water and salt. Beat with rotary beater.
Add coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° until custard is set and crust is browned.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil 3 minutes the pineapple and sugar. Add lemon Jell-O. Stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese. Stir until combined. Cool. Fold in apples, walnuts, celery and whipped topping. Pour into 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: hot salad or bacon dressing *
directions: *From the "Friendly Club" recipes of Past Matrons circa 1975.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Grease 1 baking pan with melted butter or margarine. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, and baking soda together in mixing bowl.
With pastry blender or fork, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine buttermilk and yeast water.
Add to flour mixture; stir with fork until moistened.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Roll dough out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2 inch biscuit cutter, dipping cutter into flour between cuts.
Press cutter straight down without twisting for straight-sided evenly shaped biscuits.
Place close together in prepared pan.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise 1 hour (dough does not double in size).
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned. Brush tops with butter or margarine while hot.
Yields:
Makes about 30-40 biscuits.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well. Roll into small balls. Chill it a while. Can use melting chocolate for coating.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Add condensed milk; whip until smooth.
Add vanilla flavor and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into cracker pie crust.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.
After crust and filling has chilled, place strawberries on pie and top with glaze.
Caution:
If filling is not chilled, strawberries will sink to bottom of crust.

title: skillet pork lo mein(makes about 4 servings;  consider doubling recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, blend juice, soy sauce, oil, sugar and ginger;
add
pork.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour (if possible).
In skillet, add pork and marinade; simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into two greased bread pans and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: arkansas millionaire candy
directions: In a double boiler, melt caramels with Pet milk.
Add pecans. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Leave overnight.

title: low-fat diabetic apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll one-half pastry and fit into pie pan.
Fill with apples.
In small saucepan, heat apple juice to boiling.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and stir into hot juice. Add cinnamon and cook until thick.
Dot apples with butter.
Pour juice over fruit.
Cover with remaining pastry.
Prick crust. Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: baked pineapple filling
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Blend in pineapple and add bread. Bake in greased casserole in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine butter or margarine, cocoa and 1 cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add the cocoa mixture; mix until blended. Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all.
Toss lightly and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato, broccoli, mushroom soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 2 quarts of water until tender.
Mix soup and water by directions on can.
Add to vegetables along with seasonings.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Mix cocoa with boiling water.
Let set.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff peaks form.
Sift together dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center. Add oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Cut through batter with spatula.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Increase temperature to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Invert to cool.

title: crunchy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Add more dressing, if desired. Refrigerate.
Makes 50 servings.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Ready to serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 2 layers and cool.
Prepare pudding as directed.
In punch bowl, layer as follows:
1 layer of cake (crumbled), half of vanilla pudding, half of crushed pineapple and half of cherry pie filling.
Cover with half of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
The longer the flavors mix, the better.
Keep chilled.

title: potato salad with boiled dressing
directions: Cook potatoes; combine with remaining ingredients, except celery.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add celery and Boiled Dressing.

title: macaroni ranchero
directions: Put all in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mommie's sugar cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in a bowl and beat until creamy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover the bowl and put it in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Set oven at 350°.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness, making sure you spread some flour down first.
Cut the dough into whatever shapes you want.
Bake the cookies on a greased cookie sheet for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil for 2 minutes the milk, sweetener and cocoa. Stir in 3 cups quick cooking oatmeal. Add vanilla, peanut butter or nuts. After well blended, drop on waxed paper and let cool.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix in order.
Grease 2 loaf pans or cook in coffee cans. Bake 70 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from bone and cut in large pieces (about 4 cups).
Mix nuts and chopped celery together.
Then mix the rest of ingredients together.
In a large casserole, put layer of chicken mix and layer of soup mix.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, put can of noodles over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna and chinese noodle salad
directions: Mix tuna, celery, green onions, green pepper, pimento and ripe olives.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugars.
Mix baking soda with lemon juice before adding.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberries ala gilda
directions: Combine sour cream, whipped cream, sugar, macaroon crumbs, vanilla and salt together.
Fold in strawberries.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, hard-boiled eggs and green olives.
Mix with enough mayonnaise to coat salad.

title: dream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Shape into balls and coat with Frosted Flakes.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until light brown.
Don't overcook.

title: mushroom sauerkraut soup
directions: Chop dried mushrooms, soak in cold water overnight.
Add water, sauerkraut juice and onion to pot.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours.
Add potato.
Brown flour in oil in skillet.
Stir constantly or flour will burn.
Add a cup of soup and mix constantly to make a thin zaprashka or gravy.
Add to soup.
Simmer 15 minutes more to heat through, stirring.
Add seasoning to taste.

title: white-chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Separate eggs and beat egg whites stiff. Cream margarine and sugar, then add beaten egg yolks.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with buttermilk.
Mix.
Fold in beaten egg whites with nuts and coconut.
Bake until done.

title: anna boyce's baked fresh asparagus
directions: Wash, drain and break off tough white ends of asparagus spears. Arrange in one layer in baking pan, if possible.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Combine oil and melted butter and drizzle over the asparagus, then add salt and pepper.
Cover baking pan or dish with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, unless you must arrange asparagus in 2 layers.
In that case, increase time to 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend with butter.
Fold in rest of ingredients. Bake around 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon luck dessert
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and chopped nuts.
Put this into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread out and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Warm cream cheese over low heat; remove from heat and add confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Beat all this and spread over baked mixture.
Mix lemon pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat until thick and spread over other mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except tomato sauce and cranberry sauce) and make small tight meatballs.
Broil meatballs until brown (about 5 minutes each side).
In a deep pot, add tomato sauce and cranberry sauce.
Let heat for about 5 minutes. Add cooked meatballs.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Pressure cook or microwave broccoli and onions 30 seconds or until tender (not soft and mushy).
Combine all ingredients (except sour cream) in blender.
Add sour cream and blend a few more seconds.
If you prefer a thicker soup, use less chicken broth.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 8.

title: yellow fruit punch
directions: Mix, chill and enjoy.
(May use sugar-free juices, sugar substitute and diet pop.)

title: horseradish cream sauce
directions: Beat heavy cream with an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Fold horseradish mixture into whipped cream.
Serve with standing rib beef roast or prime rib.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, saving broth to cook the wild rice. Cook wild rice according to package instructions.
Save any broth left to add later for more moisture to the mixture.
Mix the chicken, celery, onion and water chestnuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat with mixer all ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Turn freezer on and add regular milk to fill line on canister.

title: microwave mexican pizza pitas
directions: In 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine ground beef and onion.
Cook, covered, on High 6 to 8 minutes, until no pink remains.
Drain well.
Stir in sugar, chili powder and garlic salt.

title: pheby's cheese salad
directions: Put first five ingredients into the boiling vinegar and water. Cook until thick and cool.
Add cheese and sweet pickles.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over cherry layer.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat; season to taste.
Add onion and jalapeno to meat. Mix all other ingredients, except cheese.
In a greased baking dish (approximately 12 x 12-inch or similar) or in an iron skillet, pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture.
Spread meat over meal mixture; sprinkle cheese over meat.
Spread remaining cornmeal mixture over meat. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add molasses, egg and applesauce.
Beat well; stir in raisins.
Bake in Dutch oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn out; sprinkle with sugar or glaze with lemon juice and sugar.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing mix and Parmesan cheese in a bowl.
Coat both sides of chicken and place in baking dish.
Put remaining mixture on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rich cranberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup of flour with cranberries and nuts.
Fold into batter; it will be very thick.
Spoon into a 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing.
Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar before serving.
Yields about 16 servings.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Bake in 3 round cake pans.

title: chocolate butterscotch scotcheroos
directions: In a large saucepan combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring just to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix in cereal. Press in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water both Nestle morsels.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill in refrigerator (about 30 minutes).
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: sugarless health bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut up dates or prunes into saucepan. Add raisins and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 minutes. Add shortening.
Mix, then cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in preheated oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Chop onion and cook with hamburger meat.
Drain when finished cooking.
Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Take cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 to 1 can water and mix together.
Combine all of the other ingredients in a Pyrex casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° to 400°. Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.
Kids love it.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate with butter using blender.
Beat eggs well. Add powdered sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine chocolate mixture and egg mixture; add nuts.
Line 8 x 8-inch pan with wax paper.
Pour fudge into pan.
Store in refrigerator 8 hours before cutting.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add flour and cook until mixture is smooth. Add green onions and cook until tender.
Stir in beaten egg yolks, milk and seasonings. Add cheese and cook on low fire for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in crabmeat. Continue cooking on low fire for an additional 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into a large glass baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon punch
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Mix frozen juices as directed on labels.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Freeze in a gallon container.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli, drain.
Combine	soup,
milk,
mayonnaise and cheese.
Add beaten egg.
Mix in broccoli.	Top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Spread 1/2 of corn batter, then the browned meat in pan.
Top with cheese, then chop onion and jalapeno pepper.
Top with the rest of corn batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole pan with nonstick spray and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine cheese, crackers and melted margarine.
Layer in casserole 1/2 of the cracker mixture, 1/2 of the broccoli and 1/2 of the soup.
Repeat layers one more time, ending with soup.
Cover and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheezy vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine and Cheez Whiz. Combine with vegetables and
put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with crackers and drizzle margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken breast rolls
directions: Pound chicken breast pieces into 1/4-inch thickness.
Place ham and cheese over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Place in lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Combine sherry and butter; heat briefly. Pour over chicken rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Stir in the cream.
Gradually add the sugar and nuts, stirring until lump free.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, then form into small balls with your hands.
Roll in cocoa to coat.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: In a large saucepot, cook carrot, onion and celery in olive oil for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, lentils, rice, bay leaf, oregano, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Return to a simmer, cover and cook 5 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 10 cups; 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on box in an 11 x 9-inch cake pan.
After removing cake from oven, allow to cool for 5 minutes; then poke cake with a fork (entire surface).
Pour can of crushed pineapple with juice over entire surface of cake. (Spread to cover.)

title: potato salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Mix pickle juice with salt, pepper, garlic powder, mustard and mayonnaise in a small bowl. Whisk together.
Pour over potato mixture.
Serve after refrigerating for at least 1 hour.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley as a garnish.

title: ham and rye buns
directions: Mix poppy seed, mustard, butter and onion.
Spread on buns and add slices of meat and cheese.
Wrap in foil or place on pan and cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Can be made ahead of time and warmed when served.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil and mix with the jello and pudding mixes.
Chill until almost firm.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Chill.

title: harvest cornbread chicken pie
directions: Place broiler-fryer in 3 quarts water in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth, reserving broth. Let chicken cool to touch.
Bone and chop chicken.
Return chopped chicken to broth; cover and chill 8 hours.
Skim and discard fat from broth.
Remove chicken with a slotted spoon; set aside.
Bring broth to a boil; cook 50 minutes or until reduced by half.
Add sweet potatoes and cook 13 minutes or until tender; remove with a slotted spoon.
Set sweet potatoes aside.
Cook broth 20 minutes or until reduced to 1 cup.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water; stir well.
Add to broth; cook, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, bananas and milk.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan in slow oven until done (300°, about 45 minutes).

title: festive fudge foolproof
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly. Bring to a boil.
Mixture will be bubbly all over the top.
Boil and stir for 5 more minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Stir until completely melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let set.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients with electric mixer until well blended.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Bring pineapple juice and sugar to a boil.
Make thickening of water and flour; add to mixture and cook over low heat until thickened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and pinch of salt.
Spread over cake while warm.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and Karo for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix and remove from saucepan.
Put in large cake pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips.
Put on top of squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat 3 eggs slightly in a bowl.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, melted butter, vanilla and salt.
Add pecan halves and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 25 to 35 minutes longer or until lightly browned and completely puffed across top.
Cool.
Serve.

title: rich clam chowder
directions: Place bacon and onions in 3-quart glass casserole dish; cover. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add clam liquid and 1 cup water to potatoes; cover.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in flour; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes longer or until hot and begins to thicken.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: north carolina hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 23 to 28 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans and then remove.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and add taco seasoning mix.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer beef with Ranch Style beans.
Next, layer frozen tortillas, then layer with cheese.
Next with Ro-Tel tomatoes, followed by mushroom soup.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot and spicy tomato juice
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo until soft.
Do not brown.
Add basil and parsley.
Put in blender.
Add all other ingredients. Strain.
Put in boiler and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve hot in demitasee cups.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together in a large bowl.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water at 245°.
While this is cooking, put the egg whites (beaten stiff) in a bowl; pour the first mixture into this, in a fine stream.
When all is mixed, beat hard for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla; don't cover until cold.

title: sunshine salad
directions: To jello add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, pineapple, salt and carrots. Pour into square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Serve on top of lettuce leaves.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: Fill small pan about half full with oil and heat.
Shape biscuits into doughnut shape and drop into hot oil.
When lightly browned, remove from oil and let drain on paper towels.
Roll warm doughnuts in sugar-cinnamon mixture or powdered sugar.

title: baked corn
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ugly cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan, already greased.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar and spread over nuts.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked tomato relish
directions: Sprinkle chopped tomatoes with kosher salt and let stand overnight.
Drain thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients.
Ladle into jars and cap.
Must be refrigerated.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and put soda into water; add alternately into sugar mixture with flour mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: penuche icing
directions: Boil for 1 minute the sugar, milk, oleo and salt, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Beat until thick enough to spread. Add vanilla.

title: vegetable-shrimp stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add snow peas, onions and red pepper.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; stir-fry 2 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Add mushrooms.
Cook until tender and most of liquid evaporates.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red onion salad
directions: Slice onions; soak in cold water for about 20 minutes.
Drain off water; put in salad bowl with cut tomato wedges.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with chopped fresh basil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts 45 minutes or until well done. Tear from bone. Place in a pan. Add soup and water; stir. Fix stuffing according to directions on box. Spoon on top of mixture. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: rosemary chicken]
directions: Pat chicken dry.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika over chicken.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.
Do not add salt.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Place bacon slices in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in raw rice; add chicken.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Combine soup and water and pour over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: old fashioned spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, salt and flour.
Sift three times.
To the creamed mixture, add the egg and mix well.
Alternately add the flour mixture and the milk.
Mix all together.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 10 to 15 servings.

title: turkey cacciatore
directions: Rinse turkey.
Place in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add spaghetti sauce, wine, green pepper and onion.
Bring to a boil; turn down heat.
Cover.
Simmer 2 hours.
Remove turkey from broth.

title: lazy cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased 2-quart casserole.
Brown together hamburger and onion; salt and pepper.
Add rice, soup and water; mix.
Heat through and pour over cabbage.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is tender at 325°.

title: self-crust pumpkin pie
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in 2 pie plates sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400° until well brown.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Mix together and frost cooled bars.

title: lilly's apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and cinnamon with 1/4 cup apple juice, making a paste; set aside.
Simmer apples in remaining juice until apples look transparent.
Mix with thickener, cook until clear and pour into unbaked crust.
Top with crumb topping.

title: busy-day cake
directions: In a bowl combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, margarine or butter, egg and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute. Pour batter into a greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into a baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well and pour into crust and get cold.

title: onion-baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup mix with bread crumbs.
Dip chops in eggs, then bread crumb mixture, coating well.
Place in lightly greased large shallow baking pan and drizzle, if desired, with melted butter.
Bake, turning once, 1 hour or until chops are done.
Makes about 8 servings.
tags: Recipe Secrets golden onion soup mix

title: martha washington chocolate balls
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Mix with milk and work in sugar, coconut and pecans with hands.
Shape into balls the size of a small walnut.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes or longer.
Melt paraffin in top of double boiler over hot water.
Add chocolate and stir well until dissolved.
Dip coconut and pecan balls into chocolate with a fork and lay on waxed paper until hardened.

title: pastitsio
directions: Brown together beef, onion and garlic.
Add spices, tomato sauce and wine.
Bring to a boil, stirring in one egg. Melt butter.
Stir in flour and add 1 1/2 cup milk and cook until thick.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Gradually stir into 2 beaten eggs and add 1/2 the cheese. Mix macaroni with remaining eggs, milk and cheese.
Layer macaroni and meat mixtures in an 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with extra cinnamon, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spritz
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco and sugar in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer.
Beat in egg, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Work in flour until blended.
Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased baking sheets in desired shapes.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Cool slightly before removing to cooling racks.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: quick stir-fry
directions: Place oil in frypan; stir-fry the ingredients on high heat and add meat.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add the eggs, pumpkin and water.
Combine the flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Blend the dry ingredients into the batter a little at a time.
Stir in the nuts and raisins.

title: fresh peach chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water and set aside.
Combine the slightly beaten egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, mashed peaches, salt and lemon juice in the top of a double boiler.
Cook over simmering water until mixture is slightly thickened and coats a metal spoon. Remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Cool until mixture begins to set.
Add almond extract.

title: mincemeat prize cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Stir together dry ingredients, gradually add to shortening mixture. Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.

title: swan river chili
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight.
Drain; cover with cold water and simmer until beans are tender, about 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Saute green peppers in hot oil until tender.
Add onions and cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and parsley.
In another skillet, melt butter and add beef and pork.
Cook and stir 15 minutes or until crumbly and brown.
Add meat to onion mixture and stir in chili powder.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add meat mixture to beans along with salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Remove cover and simmer 30 minutes longer.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna pate(must be made ahead)
directions: Mix the cream cheese with chili sauce, parsley, onions and Tabasco.
Gradually add tuna and sour cream.
Place in mold or bowl to shape.
Chill 3 hours.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Use broth to boil noodles.
Mix noodles, chicken and all soups together.
Melt butter and pour over bread crumbs.
Put soup mixture in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Dip sliced eggplant in flour, fry in oil until brown and drain on paper towel.
In a separate bowl combine cheeses.
Add oregano, basil, pepper and garlic and mix well.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Filling:
In medium saucepan, combine the 6 candy bars, marshmallows and milk; heat and stir over medium-low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.

title: aunt jan's sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion in a bit of oil.
Push to side of pan.
