Cook hamburger; drain off any fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Cook pinto beans until tender with 1 teaspoon salt.
Mash beans and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. Shield crust with aluminum foil first 35 minutes.
Decorate with pecan halves, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sauteed spinach
directions: Wash spinach and blanch in boiling water for 2 minutes. Remove spinach and place in an ice water bath for 1 minute.
Drain spinach and squeeze dry.
Heat olive oil and butter in a saute pan over medium heat.
Add garlic and spinach and saute 2 to 3 minutes just until garlic is lightly browned and spinach warmed through. Serve immediately.

title: stromboli
directions: Oil lightly a cookie sheet.
Spread thawed dough.
Mix 1 egg with 1 teaspoon oregano and spread 1/2 mixture on dough.
Layer cheese and pepperoni over dough.
Roll.
Brush remaining egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen with plenty of parsley, onion, celery and seasoning. Cool in broth; cut in bite size pieces.
Cook vermicelli according to directions on package.
Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and mushrooms.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Heat oil, then mix in flour and milk a little at a time.
Mix in cheese and tuna.
Then mix in cooked noodles, drained.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Boil 1 minute vinegar, sugar, oil and soy sauce and cool. Saute lightly butter, noodles and almonds and pour over mixture of cabbage and onions.
Add vinegar, sugar mix and marinate 1/2 hour before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain some of fat.
Add tomatoes, water and rest of ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours over medium heat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add water and soup; stir together.
Add Cheez Whiz.
In large casserole dish, mix the broccoli, instant rice (dry) and the onion flakes.
Mix together; pour cheese mixture over this.
Stir; bake at 350° until mixture becomes bubbly.

title: brown rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a pan.
Let boil on the stove for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: chili with macaroni
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion, brown sugar and seasoning (salt, etc.).
Add the beans and stir the cooked macaroni and meat mixture together with catsup or tomato juice.
Let it simmer for 5 minutes and it is ready to serve.
Use less catsup if using bought catsup.
Chili powder or other seasonings may be added.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add milk and sugar.
Reduce heat and cook until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and marshmallow whip.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cool.

title: orange jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pop; mix well.
Put into 9 x 13 pan.
Refrigerate until syrupy.
Beat in Cool Whip; add mandarin oranges.
Add crushed pineapple.
Put into bowl. Refrigerate until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; drain off fat.
Spread ketchup over meat loaf; place back in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips and coat with flour.
Drain the pineapple chunks and save the juice.
Heat oil and brown the chicken.
Add pineapple chunks, cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce, juice from pineapple chunks and canned pineapple juice to make 2 cups in all.
Pour mixture into pan of chicken and heat until sauce thickens (approximately 1/2 hour).
Serve over rice.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast	in water and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Warm milk and shortening.
Add
eggs and 4 1/2 cups of flour, 1 cup of sugar and salt.
Mix and add yeast.
Add 4 1/2 cups more of flour.
Let rest 1/2 hour and then add remaining flour.
Turn out onto floured
board
and knead for 5 minutes.
Shape into ball and place
in
well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover loosely and
let
rise
in
warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down
and
shape
into
rolls as desired.
I use about 1/2 of dough
for	caramel
rolls.
Make
the
following Caramel recipe and divide	into
three 9 x 13-inch pans.
Roll out dough.	Spread with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly
roll style.	Cut into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Lay each slice
onto caramel mixture.
Let rise again until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks margarine for no less than 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Add one layer of sliced bananas.
Top with Dream Whip.
Garnish with Hershey's chocolate syrup and maraschino cherries.
Use one garnish or a combination.
Set in refrigerator until chilled.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water to cover until tender. Mix together sugar, flour, egg yolks and enough water to mix. Add to raisins and boil until thickens. Remove from heat and add sour cream and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients;
pour in baking dish.
Spread with thin sliced bacon.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix dough until smooth.
Tear in half.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thin.
Use round cookie cutter and cut out circles.
Fill with cooked hamburger/onion mixture or other leftover meats, chopped and seasoned.
Boil in water for approximately 10 minutes.
Serve with a sauce of mushroom soup and sour cream, or fry gently in margarine in a frying pan.
Makes about 18 (3-inch) pierogis.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together peanut butter, sugar and milk with a mixer until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
(Optional: Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate shavings.)
Slice and serve frozen.

title: homemade diet jello
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Add Kool-Aid, sweetener and boiling water; stir.
Cool well.
Partially chill.
Add fruit desired.
No calories.

title: red beans(serves 25!)
directions: Wash beans and soak for 2 hours.
(This it not really necessary.)
Chop all vegetables.
Smother onions, bell peppers, celery and ham seasoning in skillet with small amount of oil. Beans should be placed in large pot.
Fill 3/4 with water.
When water comes to a boil, add onions, celery, bell peppers and ham seasoning.
Slice sausage very thin.
Cook sausage in skillet. Throw the grease away and add sausage to the bean pot.
Cover and cook on low flame for approximately 2 1/2 hours.
Watch carefully and add water if needed.
Serve on rice!!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple; let sit for 1 minute.
Put in remaining ingredients.
Chill well and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and onions. Chill. Shape into balls. Roll into nuts.

title: lemon sage chicken
directions: Place 1 chicken breast between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Pound to 1/2-inch thickness.
Repeat with each breast. Mix rest of ingredients in a large shallow glass dish.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours.
Barbecue at medium-high heat, frequently brushing with marinade.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Add bananas, remaining flour and vanilla; blend well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.
Salt each and place in drainer for 1 hour.
Wipe dry.
Oil cookie sheets and arrange eggplant slices on it.
Brush top with a bit of oil and broil slices until brown; turn and broil other side.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Cook with candy thermometer until 300° (hard crack), then add 1/2 teaspoon of food coloring and 1 teaspoon of oil flavoring. Pour over powdered sugar which has been leveled in large cookie sheet.

title: coca-cola bing cherry salad
directions: Drain
fruit
and
reserve
juice;
measure and heat to boiling to
dissolve
gelatin.
Add
as much of the 2 colas as needed for required liquid (4 cups total).
Cool until syrupy. Cut cherries
into
fourths and cut pecans into large pieces. When gelatin
has
begun to set, stir in fruit and nuts.
Pour into oiled
ring mold and congeal.
When ready to serve, fill center of ring with cottage cheese.

title: baked rice and vegetables
directions: Place alternate layers of rice and vegetables in a greased baking dish, sprinkling each layer with salt and pepper.
Add milk and lay slices of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bacon is well done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dilly cucumber
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Yields 1-1/2 cups of dressing.

title: super easy kiss cookies
directions: Mix condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Press kisses on while hot.

title: pear streusel pie
directions: Boil pears in 1 cup water for 10 minutes.
Drain and save liquid for sauce.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add lemon rind, juice and 1 cup cooking liquid from pears.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Put pears in uncooked pie crust; cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping and bake in a hot 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash and onions in large container with 4 tablespoons salt. Place ice on top and let stand for at least 1 hour or overnight. Drain off saltwater. Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and peppers to onion and squash. Bring to a boil. Add pimentos. Fill sterilized hot jars. Cool and store.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine ketchup, sugar, 1 tablespoon lemon and mustard.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients and 1/3 cup ketchup mixture; mix well.
In shallow baking dish shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour; pour off fat.
Pour remaining ketchup mixture over loaf.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Garnish as desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican rice
directions: Put tomatoes, garlic, pepper in sauce pan with enough water to barely cover tomatoes.
Cook until tomatoes crack open and skin begins to peel.
Remove from water and put into blender; add onion, chicken broth, cilantro, chop or blend until you have a smooth soup like juice; set aside.
In large skillet heat olive oil on high until pan and oil is hot; add rice.
Stir constantly until rice is light brown; reduce heat to medium.
Add tomato sauce while stirring; you may add a little water if seems to be too dry.
Cover with lid; let simmer until rice is done, stirring every 5 min.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Stir before each use.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Take prepared cooking apples and put them in former fruit pickled juice.
Pour all together and bring to a boil.
Simmer until they can easily be pierced with a straw.
The result is pickles with an elusive flavor and as pretty as they are novel.

title: clinton cookie
directions: The Best Foods Test Kitchen has created a cookie in honor of President Clinton that can be decorated with stars, stripes, or a Bill Clinton caricature.
The idea for combining peanut butter and bananas into a Clinton cookie was made at the suggestion of an employee at the Skippy Peanut Butter Manufacturing Plant in Little Rock, Arkansas.
The company said peanut butter and bananas are one of President Clinton's favorite sandwich combos.

title: fancy rabbit(this is good, but takes a while to prepare.)
directions: Place rabbit in baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with mixture of onions, wine, water and vinegar.
Place in refrigerator for 2 days.
Pat rabbit dry.
Flour and fry in butter until brown.
Add 1/2 cup of marinade liquid and bring to boil. Cover and simmer until rabbit is tender.
Remove the meat; add flour to liquid.
After liquid is thickened to a gravy, stir in sour cream and pour over rabbit.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Set aside. Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter by one tablespoon at a time.
With your fingers, crumble peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Put one layer of peanut butter mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Cover it with half the pudding.
Do another layer of peanut butter mixture.
Then repeat pudding on top again.
Top with Cool Whip. Then sprinkle any peanut butter mixture left on top.
Refrigerate. Enjoy!

title: florida orange melts
directions: In a food processor, process the wafers with 1 cup of the pecans until finely ground.
Add together the powdered sugar and orange zest and mix well until evenly incorporated.
Add the orange juice concentrate, orange liqueur and corn syrup and mix until blended.
Finely chop the remaining pecans and spread them in a shallow bowl.
Spread coconut in a shallow bowl.
Form the mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in either the pecans or the coconut to coat.
Let cookies mellow for at least 4 hours before eating.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal into a large bowl (large Tupperware bowl with lid works well).
Set aside.
In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals.
Mix until well coated.
Add powdered sugar. Seal securely.
Shake until well coated. Add more powdered sugar, if needed.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Put potatoes and water in 2-quart casserole dish or pie plate. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High until fork-tender, about 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after 1/2 time.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and set potatoes aside.
Place margarine in a bowl and microwave until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients to butter.
Pour over potatoes.

title: herbed broccoli
directions: Trim large leaves and tough ends from broccoli; wash broccoli. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Heat 1 inch water in medium saucepan.
Add broccoli; cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for about 10 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add basil, oregano, salt, garlic and tomatoes.
Heat for about 1 minute, stirring frequently, until hot.
Pour over broccoli and toss.

title: green beans and potatoes
directions: In a small pot, empty green beans with liquid contents. Add extra 1 cup of water.
Drop in bouillon cube and add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil. When boiling starts, add potato cubes. Cook until almost all of water is gone and green beans are very tender and potato is done.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Fill pastry shell with peaches.
Combine other ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: wellington meat loaf for two
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with 1/2 can brown gravy and use the other half when serving.
Put in loaf pan and top with crescent rolls.
Brush some butter on top of rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Add Wesson oil; mix well.
Sprinkle onion soup mix.
Mix well.
Bake in covered casserole dish 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake to melt cheese or until brown.

title: snow-white turkey salad
directions: Combine the turkey, celery, green pepper and onion in a bowl. Set aside.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, whipped cream, bouillon granules, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold into turkey-vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Mound turkey salad on crisp lettuce and circle with desired garnishes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: birds
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil the chicken breasts for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Cut chicken into 8 pieces.
Place a piece of chicken in a crescent roll and seal all edges.
Continue until all rolls are used. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip soup and broth until smooth. Pour over rolls.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 4 to 5 minutes more.
Remove from oven.
Serve with sour cream.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: In a medium glass bowl, begin to make layers with fruit. Continue to layer until the layers have been done twice or according to the serving size desired.
(Add no sugar.)

title: tomato pie
directions: Line large pie pan or 11 1/4 x 7 1/2-inch dish with crescent rolls.
Slice the tomatoes in pan until 3/4 full.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, basil, chives and onion over tomatoes.
Mix mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Pour on the tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: saucy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and salt.
Shape into 50 meatballs. Place in shallow pan.
Broil or bake until browned.
Turn over. Spoon off fat.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Save some crackers for top.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add boiling water and lemon flavoring to lemon jello.
Cool.
Then add cheese and sugar mixture.
Whip Milnot and then add to jello and cheese mixture.
Add crushed pineapple. Pour over crackers and top with remaining crumbs.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 7-up.
Fold in 7-up. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2 ungreased bread pans or 1 Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: raisin pie filling
directions: Cover raisins with water and cook with lemon juice until tender.
Then add brown sugar.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add raisins.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
For a 2-crust pie, 1 big one or 2 small ones.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Put all ingredients except nutmeg into blender container in order listed.
Cover and blend at low speed until mixed.
Strain into punch cups and garnish with nutmeg.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Use coarse blade on grinder.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl, sprinkle with salt, cover with cold water and let stand for 4 hours.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a 4-quart saucepan.
Cook on stove, stirring constantly as this burns easily.
After it starts a rolling boil, let it boil for five minutes, no longer; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add all the rest of the ingredients at once.
Mix well.
Put in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Have butter soft, then mix in sugar and vanilla.
Sift in flour and salt and stir into sugar and fat mixture along with nuts.
Form small 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 17 minutes in 400° oven.
Roll in sugar. Cool.
Roll again in sugar.

title: prawn cocktail (shrimp cocktail)england
directions: Half fill 4-6 Sundae dishes with the lettuce, divide the shrimp between the dishes, pile them on top of the lettuce.

Set aside. Blend together the mayonnaise, ketchup, lemon juice, salt, milk and tabasco, adding enough ketchup to make it a nice pink color. Spoon this over the top of the shrimp, sprinkle with paprika and garnish with cucumber, tomato and lemon slices. Serve with thin slices of buttered brown bread.

title: whoopie pie filling
directions: Mix all together until fluffy.

title: peanut butter and oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until a rolling boil for 1 minute. Add dash of salt, vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper.

title: squash dressing
directions: Chop onions and cook in one stick margarine until onions are clear.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine onions and margarine with slightly beaten eggs.
Add soup, squash and bread crumbs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.

title: sugar-free cocoa mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: turkey-vegetable medley
directions: Cut turkey into 8 slices.
Place turkey in large skillet; may need to overlap slices.
Combine frozen vegetables and salad dressing.
Pour over turkey.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Makes 4 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix the ingredients; pour into a chafing dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: chinese duck sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Mix together; pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes enough sauce for 2 to 3 pounds of chicken pieces.
Great served over rice pilaf.

title: orange delite salad
directions: Mix orange Jell-O dry with cottage cheese; mix very well. Drain oranges and pineapple well.
Cut oranges into tiny pieces. Mix well with cottage cheese mixture; add Cool Whip.
Mix well. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving (the longer the better).

title: swiss steak with rice
directions: Mix flour with salt, paprika and pepper. Rub steak with garlic and roll in seasoned flour. Brown onions slightly in melted shortening.
Remove onions and sear the meat on both sides and put into a greased casserole.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Cook onions until tender. Add flour and salt; stir.
Add chicken broth.
Cook until thick. Add chicken and peas and carrots.
Cook until bubbly.
Pour mixture into pan.
Top with pie crusts.
Bake until crusts are brown.

title: chocolate angel food
directions: Cook for three minutes over a double boiler, stirring constantly; add pinch of salt and vanilla at the end.
If you have any left over, refrigerate and then place container in hot water to warm up to spreading consistency.
Recipe will not work in the microwave.

title: hasty pudding biscuits
directions: Make the Hasty Pudding and when lukewarm, add dissolved yeast and mix well. Then add the egg, shortening, spice and molasses. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Knead well. Let rise overnight. Shape into biscuits. Let rise until light and bake in hot oven (400°) about 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice-a-roni(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: Spray dish.
In pot, use 2 tablespoons oil.
Put Rice-A-Roni in pot.
Stir until it browns.
In bowl, mix 1 can of mushroom soup mix.
Add 1 1/2 cans of water.
Mix package of seasonings and add; bring to boil.

title: grandma dicke's slumgunion venison
directions: In pressure cooker, place meat, spices and 1/4 cup to 1 cup water.
Cook for 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
In large skillet, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and vinegar until smooth. Add meat juice.
Break meat into 1-inch pieces and add.
Serve hot over rice, baked potatoes or mashed potatoes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo.
Cook until small ball forms.
Add vanilla and marshmallows.
Beat! Beat!
Beat! Frost layers.
If you cook too long, add a little milk and beat.

title: potato surprise
directions: Butter casserole dish, then start to layer:
cleaned, sliced potatoes, onions, cheese and ham or Spam.
Top all this with cheese and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until potatoes are done.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in jar or other tightly covered container.
To serve, place 1/3 cup mix in a mug; fill with hot water and stir well.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine jello, eggs, water and Wesson oil with dry cake mix. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add strawberries; mix well. Pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium sized bowl. Refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until sugar is dissolved. Pour into ice cream freezer.
Can add extra sweet milk to bring mixture even with fill line on freezer.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: In glass or pottery bowl, combine the diced watermelon, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Mix together well and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove and force the mixture through a sieve or puree in electric blender.
Very gradually add milk, then salt and mix well.
Place in dry refrigerator trays and freeze until the mixture is firm along the sides and mushy in the center.
Remove from trays, scraping their sides.
Empty into a bowl and beat well.
If too pale, add a few drops of food coloring (red).
Add the cognac or wine.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites and return to freezer for at least 5 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix one cup hot water and cranberry sauce in blender.
(If you would like pecans, add to cranberry sauce mixture).
Dissolve Jello in one cup hot water.
Add cranberry mixture to Jello.
Put half of mixture into pan and chill for 30 minutes in fridge.
Once the Jello is firm, spread sour cream over the top.
Add other half of Jello mixture.
Place in fridge to chill.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Add onion to bacon drippings; cook over low heat until tender, about 3 minutes. Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and bacon; cook and stir until boiling.
Place lettuce in large salad bowl; pour hot dressing over lettuce and toss until well coated.
Garnish with radish slices and chopped egg.
Serves 6.
Do not chill salad before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl. Add milk, water and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients; beat into egg mixture until smooth. Heat oil to 375°. Cover bottom of funnel with finger; ladle 1/2 cup batter into funnel. Hold funnel above skillet. Remove finger and in spiral motion, let batter fall into hot oil. Fry 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion, mix with canned chili.
Spread on bottom of oblong dish.
Spread sour cream carefully on top.
Lay cheese slices on top of sour cream.
Crush Doritos and sprinkle on top of cheese enough to cover entire dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Top with salsa (optional).

title: uova con sparagi(eggs with asparagus)
directions: Cut asparagus in 1-inch lengths.
Drop in pan when oil is hot. Cook for 10 minutes or until tender.
Lower heat.
Beat eggs and fold into pan.
Stir until cooked to your desire.
Serve hot. Good on Italian roll or bread.
Serves many.

title: macaroni and cheese soup
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain; rinse with cold water.
Drain and set aside.
Melt margarine in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots, celery and onions.
Cook and stir until tender.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine milk and cheese in heavy Dutch oven.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts, being careful it does not stick or scorch.
Stir in chicken broth and pepper. Combine cornstarch with water; mix until smooth.
Stir into milk mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Stir in macaroni, vegetable mixture, corn and peas.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Yields 8 cups.

title: foiled chicken breast
directions: Place one breast in a large piece of aluminum foil and put each ingredient on it.
Wrap tightly and place on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Repeat for each breast. (Bake together.)

title: kooky clay
directions: Combine flour, salt and water in bowl; mix with wooden spoon until smooth.
Test consistency by pressing between fingers.
Add small amount of flour if too mushy or several drops of water if too dry.
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.
Warm at room temperature before using. Shape as desired, paint with water-based paint and allow to air-dry.
Spray with clear acrylic to seal and keep.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: First, put your peppers in boiling water after you have split them in halves.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cook your 1 cup of rice in 2 cups of water for 15 minutes (covered).
Remove from stove and add to the ground beef and other ingredients.
Stuff the peppers; put in long pan and add tomato catsup on top of each pepper.
Now pour around the peppers 1 quart of tomato juice.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until most of the tomato juice has cooked into the peppers.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain well.
In a large saucepan, mix beef and other ingredients, except macaroni and cheese.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add macaroni.
Serve in bowls.
Pass shredded Cheddar cheese as a topping.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter over low heat in baking pan.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix well. Arrange shrimp in single layer in sauce. Spoon sauce over shrimp.
Broil 8 minutes.
Remove from broiler and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Broil at high
heat for 3 minutes.

title: hot herbed tomatoes
directions: Choose even-sized, rather small tomatoes. Place in a bowl; cover with boiling water. Leave 30 seconds and pour off water. Peel off skins. Heat butter in a frying pan; add celery and garlic and saut 5 minutes. Add tomatoes; sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar and spoon butter over them. Cover and cook gently for 5 minutes. Sprinkle on herbs; baste again with butter and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, basting often.
Spoon sauce once more over tomatoes before serving. Serve hot with roast poultry, beef, veal and grilled meats. Serves 4 to 5.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes 30 minutes.
Add onions and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cook on low heat until thick.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and let drain.
Chop all vegetables and combine them with macaroni.
Combine canned milk, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over macaroni and vegetables.
Add shredded cheese and stir.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix mayonnaise, capers, green onion, parsley, pimiento and lemon juice.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours before serving. Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: macaroni-beef skillet supper
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute meat, onion and garlic in oil until the meat loses its pink color and the onions are tender. Add pepper, tomato sauce, catsup, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and Italian seasoning.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Melt
margarine and mix in chopped pecans and flour.
Press down in 12 x 1/2-inch Pyrex baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour, salt, butter, cream cheese and sour cream until a crumbly mixture.
Shape pastry into 4 disks.
Wrap; chill for 2 hours to 2 days.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg substitute and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and baking soda; mix well. Cover; chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press into 1/4-inch thick circles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Melt chocolate pieces as package directs; stir in vegetable shortening, mixing until smooth.
Top each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Chill until set. Store tightly covered.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in buttermilk and roll in the crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes in foil covered shallow pan.
Remove foil, pour melted margarine over chicken and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve chicken and juice over rice.

title: never fail caramels
directions: Stir constantly over medium heat.
Cook 13 to 15 minutes after boiling starts.
Pour over nuts in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mark while warm.

title: pepper steak over rice
directions: Brown steak; put seasonings in.
Add diced onion, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain and add tomatoes and tomato sauce. Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: texas hash
directions: Fry onion, green pepper and hamburg.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients and store in container.
For 1 cup of cocoa, mix 1/3 cup chocolate and 2/3 cup hot water.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers, onion and green peppers.
Add uniodized salt. Let stand about an hour.
Drain and add the remaining ingredients.
Keeps in the refrigerator several days.

title: peanut butter brownie cups
directions: Mix brownies according to directions.
Fill paper-lined or foil-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Remove wrappers from candy.
Set one in each muffin cup and press down until batter meets the top edge of the candy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; take grease off.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; heat on low until warm.
Cook lasagna noodles in large pan.
Add some vegetable oil to water so noodles don't stick; stir while cooking.
Run cold water over noodles; let drain.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay noodles down on bottom of pan so pan is covered, then spread 1/2 of your meat sauce over noodles.
Stir in 1 egg to cottage cheese; spread 1/2 of cottage cheese evenly over spaghetti sauce, then sprinkle 1 1/2 packages Mozzarella cheese over cottage cheese.
Do your second layer of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese again.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in oil. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups. Stir until smooth. Add Velveeta cheese. Cook until cheese is melted. Add rice, peas, olives and chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy cake
directions: Select your favorite flavor and brand of cake mix. Spray desired size pan or pans with cooking spray. Prepare according to package directions with the following modifications.

Add 1 tablespoon of flour to the dry mix and blend well. Substitute an equal amount of Mott's natural applesauce for vegetable oil and substitute an equal amount of egg whites for the whole eggs. Cool in pan or pans on rack. Remove when cool. Frost cake and garnish with fresh berries, if desired.
Makes 16 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together, adding the noodles last. Bake 15 minutes at 450°. Top with 1 cup of Cheddar cheese, grated. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: light chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin tins or 8-inch round pans with cooking spray.
In bowl, stir flour, cocoa and baking soda. In another bowl, mix oil and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla; stir. Add wet ingredients to dry.
Blend well.
Bake 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool and frost if you wish.

title: pork roast with apricots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim fat off pork.
Using a sharpening steel or similar tool, poke a hole through the center of the roast, end to end.
Insert the apricots into the hole, pushing them in with your fingers.
This gives you a pretty patch of orange when you slice the roast.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 3/4 butter.
Add stuffing.
Put in layer of stuffing in casserole.
Add squash, soup and sour cream.
Top remaining stuffing.
Add rest of the butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and chill.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks.
Place bacon on rack in microwavable dish; cover with paper towel.
Microwave for 3-4 minutes, or until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
Reserve fat in dish.
Add chopped onion to bacon fat, and microwave 1 1/2-2 1/2 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt, celery seed and pepper. Mix in water and vinegar.
Microwave 5 1/2-7 minutes, until mixture thickens, stirring twice during cooking time.
Crumble bacon into mixture.
Stir in potatoes.
Microwave 5-7 minutes. Serve warm.

title: elder blossom wine
directions: Pour the boiling water over the blossoms and sugar.
Add the juice and rind of the lemon.
Let cool to lukewarm and add one yeast cake.
Let stand for 48 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add ground turkey and fry until brown.
Add salt, pepper, onions, green pepper and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash medley
directions: Parboil squash (zucchini for 3 minutes; yellow crooknecks 5 minutes).

title: banana cake
directions: Combine all ingredients
and
pour
into
a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Brown ground chuck and drain. Combine all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 325° in oven dish sprayed with vegetable oil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until squash is tender.
Drain well.
Put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Layer squash, Cheez-Its and grated cheese.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over top and bake 30 to 45 minutes on 400°.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and vegetables till tender.
Add ham.
Blend 2 c. milk, 2 Tbsp. flour and 1 c. sour cream.
Stir into soup. Yummy!

title: beef and vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, then drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
In large mixing bowl, combine pasta, zucchini, beef strips, artichoke hearts, cubed cheese and chopped pepper.

title: aunt hazel's coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and flour and stir until smooth and creamy.
Sprinkle coconut in bottom of unbaked pie crust. Pour egg mixture on top.
Pour melted butter or margarine evenly over the top of coconut and egg mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
This is an old-fashioned custard pie.
Changing the directions as given in any way will probably change the taste, but I really don't know why this happens.
This pie is delicious hot or cold.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Spread pecan halves on cookie sheet.
Stir together honey and vinegar.
Drizzle over pecans.
Place in 300° oven for 15 minutes. Stir pecans.
Stir melted butter and seasoned salt together. Drizzle over pecans and bake 10 more minutes.
Refrigerate any leftovers in jar.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni and
water in 9-inch microproof baking dish. Double wrap tightly
with plastic wrap and cook on High 9 to 10 minutes or
until
macaroni
is cooked but still firm. Pour off any remaining
water,
stir
in cheese, butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Cover
and
cook
on High 6 minutes stirring once. Cooking time 15 to 16 minutes.

title: hand dipped chocolates
directions: Mix together sugar and butter; stir in condensed milk.
Add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and mix well.
Divide into 3 to 5 bowls and make varieties:

title: crab or shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and fish with fork.
Spread on flat plate, making it approximately 1/2 inch thick.
Spread cocktail sauce on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: In a deep pan greased with olive oil, brown the ground chuck with the finely chopped onion and garlic. This should take about 20 minutes. Next add the spices and tomato sauce and paste and simmer for 2 hours. Take the bay leaves out.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: In large saucepan, cover potatoes with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel and core apples; cut into 1/4-inch rings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, pineapple, milk, coconut and pecans. Add lemon juice last.
Divide into two pie crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Put in a single layer in a flat pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake in 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mama's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour; stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: deep dish chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in water in microwave.
Blend in Cool Whip. Put in 10-inch graham cracker deep dish pie crust.
Chill and serve.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: grandma griffin's peanut brittle candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water, bring to a boil.
When boiling nicely, add the raw peanuts.
Cook until syrup begins to turn light brown and peanuts begin to pop.
Add baking soda just before pouring up.
Stir well, then pour into a large buttered pan.
Let cool, then break into small pieces.

title: homemade beef stew
directions: Cut up beef and roll in flour; brown in the oil.
Put in a crock-pot and cook overnight with 2 cups water. Dice the potatoes. Put in crock-pot the next morning.
When the potatoes are done, add the carrots, corn, peas, gravy and onions. Cook over low heat about 4 hours, adding a little water when needed.

title: patio bread
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Mix remaining ingredients all together and spread half of mixture on each half of bread.
Wrap each half in foil and heat in 300° oven for 20 minutes or until all is melted on bread.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
oleo;
add flour, salt, cocoa, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch (sprayed with Pam) pan. Bake at 300°
for
30 to 35 minutes.
Take out of oven, spread marshmallows on cake.
Put	back
in oven until they melt (not for very long).
Cool before icing.

title: chocolate marble cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in egg yolks one at a time until well blended.
Combine gelatin and water in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir until well dissolved; cool slightly.
Beat gelatin mixture into batter.
Combine 3/4 cup batter and melted chocolate.
Whip cream until soft peaks form. Fold 1/2 into chocolate batter and 1/2 into vanilla batter with large spoon; alternate batters into crust until all batter is used.
Use a knife to swirl batter to form marble pattern.
Chill for 3 hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: fudgy applesauce cake
directions: Mix all together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Yields 9 large servings.

title: green goddess dip
directions: Advance preparation:
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, chives, anchovy paste, lemon juice and garlic.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: german style salad(preparation time:  1 hour.  makes 4 servings.)
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until brown.
Add onions and flour; cook until bubbly.
Add next 6 ingredients; bring to boil. Cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in potatoes and parsley gently, coating potatoes with sauce.
Bring to boil; remove from heat and serve immediately.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours.
(This soup can be pureed, if desired; I do!)

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Add enchilada sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Heat chopped chiles and soup with 1/2 can of water.
Grease baking dish.
Line with quartered tortillas.
Layer meat mixture then soup mixture then grated cheese (1/2 of each).
Repeat with tortillas through cheese. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: romantic fruit salad
directions: Slice oranges in circle; pull apart in triangles. Twirl together gently. Chill in clear glass bowl. Goes great with turkey or chicken.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with bite size pieces of chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake 10 more minutes at 350°.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Do not shred cabbage.
Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Heat remaining 6 ingredients, just until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Yields about 1/2 gallon of slaw.
This may be kept in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour; mix.
Add extract and 7-Up; mix.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake approximately 1 to 2 hours, depending on ovens.
Will be nicely brown on top.

title: butterscotch icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon juice. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in chopped pecans; mix well.
Shape into rolls and roll in waxed paper.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: fruited cobbler
directions: Make crumbs by combining flour, sugar, baking soda, butter and margarine.
Mix well with pastry cutter.
Put half of crumbs in an 8 x 13-inch pan; do not pat crumbs down.
Put the fruit pie filling on next and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crumbs are light brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients in salt for 3 hours and cover with ice cubes.
Drain, don't wash.
Boil remaining ingredients; after it boils, add vegetables.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sarah's oven baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Mix flour and bread crumbs together in plastic bag.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Pour margarine into baking pan.
Shake chicken in bag, then coat chicken in margarine.
Put chicken in broiler; brown chicken on both sides.
Remove from broiler.
Take chicken out of pan and place in baking dish.
Add 1 cup of water to pan.
Mix and pour over chicken in dish.
Add parsley flakes. Cover dish and bake t 350° for 30 minutes.
Chicken should melt in your mouth.

title: fritter batter
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Dip fruit, chunks of cheese or fish fillets in batter.
Deep fry at 375° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve warm.

title: quick cherry pudding
directions: Mix cherries and sugar.
Let stand while preparing batter. Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Pour cherries on top of batter and pour boiling water over all.
Bake about 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve with heavy cream.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Remove crusts
on bread.
Butter and cube bread slices. Place bread and
sausage in baking dish.	Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour
before baking.
Place in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: forbidden city lemon spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into 1 rib pieces.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, lemon peel and juice, soy sauce, garlic and red pepper in large bowl, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add ribs; toss to coat lightly with sauce.
Reserving sauce, remove ribs and place in a single layer in shallow, foil lined baking pan.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Drain off excess drippings.
Brush ribs with 1/3 of reserved sauce.
Return to oven and bake uncovered 30 minutes longer, turning and brushing occasionally with remaining sauce.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place first 6 ingredients by layers in a large dish.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar over top of mayonnaise. Sprinkle grated cheese over this and then bacon bits over top. Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours before serving.

title: blueberry turnovers
directions: Prepare pastry.
Cover and chill while preparing filling.

title: spicy hot dog bites
directions: Cut each frankfurter crosswise into 5 or 6 equal pieces. Place in a chafing dish or stove top casserole over low heat.
In a small saucepan, combine currant jelly, chili sauce, mustard and onion.
Stir over low heat until jelly melts.
Pour over hot dog pieces.
Serve warm.
Makes 50 to 60 servings.

title: deviled flounder fillets
directions: Arrange in single layer, slightly overlapping in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and squeeze on lemon juice. Pour combination of rest on fish.
Bake for 15 minutes until brown.
Can be microwaved.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Crumble together brown sugar, flour, butter, salt, cinnamon or nutmeg; stir gently into sliced tomatoes.
Add 3 to 5 more pats of butter atop.
Cover with pie crust; seal.
Top with milk, cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick s'mores(kids)
directions: Layer a graham cracker with 1/2 Hershey bar and 1 large marshmallow.
Microwave on High for 15 seconds.
Top with another graham cracker.
Allow to cool for a minute or so and then serve.

title: ding-dong cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake the cake according to the package directions in two 10-inch cake pans (round).
Cool completely. While the cake is baking, mix together the flour, salt and milk and cook until very thick.

Cover with Saran Wrap and cool completely. When cake is cool and milk mixture cools, beat the Crisco and granulated sugar until light and fluffy; continue beating as you add the thickened milk mixture.
Whip until light and fluffy; add vanilla.
Split the layers of cake and place one right side up on serving tray.
Frost with 1/3 of filling; add next layer; frost with 1/3 and put on final layer and add the other 1/3.
Make sure it is stacked evenly and then frost the top and sides with the canned frosting.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips together; mix in peanuts.
Drop onto wax paper and refrigerate until set.

title: best yet pineapple salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple and jello.
Remove from stove and add buttermilk.
Chill 2 hours or until thick.
Fold in small carton of whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: coconut surprise
directions: Add flour and nuts to margarine.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spoon on crust.
Put half of coconut on cream cheese mixture.
Combine pudding and milk and beat until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cream cheese and coconut, then spread the remaining Cool Whip on the pudding.
Put the remaining coconut on the Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.
Serves 15.

title: bake and take cake
directions: Mix oats and water; let stand.
Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix alternately with oats into creamed sugars and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: toasted sesame cheese spread
directions: Pour soy sauce over cream cheese block in small dish, turning over several times to coat all sides.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours, turning cheese block often.
Remove cheese block from soy sauce and roll in sesame seed.
Refrigerate until ready to serve with crackers.
Makes 4 to 6 appetizer servings.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.

title: cranberry-raspberry tea
directions: Heat ingredients until hot.
Serve with a cinnamon stick, if desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Meanwhile, in a bowl, cut peanut butter into powdered sugar until small crumbs form.
Set aside about 2 tablespoons of crumbs.
Pour pudding over the crumbs.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pizza style meat loaf
directions: Place ground beef, green pepper, onions, seasons, egg, crumbs and half of the tomato sauce.
Mix well to form into a loaf.
Add remaining tomato sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed baked eggplant
directions: Cut eggplants in half and place in the oven at 375° in a pan with a cup of water in the bottom to steam the eggplant.
Cook until tender, about 30 minutes.
Carefully remove the pulp with a spoon so that you do not break the skin.
Brown shallots and parsley in butter over low heat.
Add shrimp, crab meat and the eggplant pulp.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir together and cook for 5 minutes.
Fill the shells.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over the top of each eggplant.
Bake at 350° until tops are browned.
Serves 4.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients with a spoon or spatula. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes. Cool before frosting.

title: open house punch
directions: Mash bananas.
Place in blender with 1/4 cup orange juice. Blend.

title: party pizza turnover
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; saute.
Stir in pizza sauce, spice mix, mushrooms and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, soda, salt and oats; mix well, then blend in sugar and butter.
Add honey, vanilla and eggs; mix at medium speed.
Mix in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes, or until a light golden brown.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Boil chicken in water (cut up thighs into 2 small pieces). Boil for approximately 30 minutes.
Add soy sauce, onion (cut up) and vinegar.
Add garlic seasoning, black pepper and bay leaf. (Do not throw water away; leave boiled water in pan.)
Cut potatoes into fours.
Add potatoes.
When potatoes are cooked, it is done.

title: diabetic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter; add sweetener, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Add flour mixture and beat well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
(Four cookies equal 1 slice bread or 3 fat exchanges.)

title: broccoli pie
directions: Cook hamburger meat with onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper; drain grease.
To the meat, add cream cheese and mushroom soup. Stir in cooked broccoli. Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: italian bread crumbs mixture
directions: Blend all together.
Can be used for any kind of breading. Also great for meat balls.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate potatoes.
Melt butter; pour over potatoes and toss lightly.
Add the eggs, sugar, molasses, milk and vanilla.
In a small bowl, mix together the sifted flour with the salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to potato mixture; stir to mix well.
Turn into a buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in low oven at 325° for about 2 1/2 hours.
During the first hour, stir several times. Cover with foil during the latter part of the baking period.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; salt and pepper to taste.
Cut or tear into small pieces.
Reserve liquid.
Place chicken in a casserole dish; add drained Veg-All and onion.
Combine soup with enough of the reserved liquid to just cover the chicken and pour in the casserole.

title: honey roasted apples
directions: Pare top third of apples; remove cores, leaving 1/2 inch of core on bottom.
Place apples in oiled baking dish.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 1/2 can of soup, mushrooms and 1/2 can onion rings; toss lightly.
Bring remainder of soup and 1/2 cup sour cream to a boil.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cut biscuits in half; arrange cut side down around top of casserole. Beat 1 egg with 1/2 cup of sour cream.
Add celery seed and salt. Pour around side on top of biscuits.
Put remaining onion rings in center of biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water with marshmallows until marshmallows are melted. Add 2 cups cold water and cool.
Add 4 sliced bananas and pineapple when thickening.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Let it become firm.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift all together until mixed well.
Store in airtight container.
To make by the cup, use 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.
Makes a great gift.

title: southern peach coffee cake
directions: In mixer bowl, combine 1/2 cup of the flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and water to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg, vanilla flavoring and another 1/2 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
By hand, stir in 3/4 cup flour to make a stiff batter.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add carrots and broth. Add chicken
and
rice.
Simmer
20 minutes.
Place in baking dish in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: awesome green beans
directions: Cook green beans according to package and drain.
Place beans in buttered casserole and sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese. Saute onion and 3 tablespoons butter; add flour.
Add sour cream. Cook to boil and pour sauce over top of Swiss cheese and beans. Melt 1/4 cup butter and add crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top of sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Blend oil, eggs and strawberries well, then add to dry mixture.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
(Can use any size pans and adjust cooking time accordingly.)
I usually use 3 (2 pound) loaf pans.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Mix salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder with flour and add next.
Add zucchini.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans and bake for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole(microwave)
directions: Cook ground beef in large casserole in microwave oven on 100% power until all red color disappears; drain most of fat off.
Add onion, tomatoes, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, salt and pepper.
Microwave until mixture reaches a boil (about 4 minutes). Remove and add cooked macaroni and mushroom soup.
Mix well. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and heat until cheese melts.

title: mom's scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until half done in water and drain. In skillet, melt butter. In a bowl, sift flour and gradually add milk; beat with a whisk until smooth and creamy. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Place Velveeta cubes in white sauce mixture. Stir until all is melted. If too thick, add more milk to make a smooth consistency. You should use close to 4 cups milk in all.

title: rum sundae sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat to low; cook, without stirring, until a candy thermometer reaches 230°.
Remove from heat, and cool slightly.
Stir in rum extract.
Serve over ice cream.
Yields 1 cup.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Use pizza pan or a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Separate rolls and spread into bottom of pan for crust.
Brown sausage; should be crumbly. Drain off grease. Spread over crust. Add hash browns and top with cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, onion, lemon juice, celery and salt and pepper.
Toss with grapes, oranges, mayonnaise and almonds. Arrange on lettuce and top with almonds and ripe olives (optional).
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add raisins and caraway
seed.
In separate bowl, beat egg and milk.
Add egg mixture to the dry ingredients.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured bread pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Use butter spatula or waxed paper to press mixture evenly into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares.
Will make 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: brunsli(christmas cookies)
directions: Put almonds in bowl.
Sieve in the powdered sugar.
Stir in cocoa, cinnamon, vanilla and Kirsch.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold egg whites into almond mixture until firm.
Wrap the dough in Saran Wrap and put it into the fridge for 1 hour.
Spread sugar onto a board.
Roll dough flat (1cm/0.4-inches).
Cut out stars (4cm/1.6-inches).
Lay them on a tray that has been lined with paper.
Leave for 4 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream and water.
In a saucepan, cook green beans and onions for 15 minutes.
Grease the bottom of casserole dish with butter.
Place green beans in first, then alternate layers with soup mixture, grated cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, then place onion rings on top and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add blueberries and lemon rind.
Toss to coat berries.
Spoon into an unbaked pie crust.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Brush a little milk on crust.
Sprinkle a little sugar on it.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes, then in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: marie's cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and syrup for 5 minutes.
Add soda. Pour mixture over popcorn and stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir once or twice while baking.

title: canned hot peppers
directions: Bring vinegar and water to a boil.
Cut ends off peppers, both tip and tops (don't remove seeds).
Put peppers in jars.
Add salt.
Pour boiling vinegar over them and seal.
There is enough brine for 2 jars.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Place in bottom of 12 x 14-inch dish.
Prepare pudding according to directions on package; add Cool Whip.
Mix together and pour over cake pieces.
Mix jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water and stir until dissolved.
Pour jello mix over other mixture.
Top with thawed strawberries.

title: vegetables alfredo
directions: Whisk the milk, cornstarch and cheese in a large saucepan until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce the heat and simmer until thick.
Stir in pepper, tarragon, thyme and parsley.
Heat olive oil in large, nonstick skillet.
Add the peas, celery, scallions, carrots and sweet peppers.
Stir-fry the vegetables until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Add sauce to veggies; mix.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Let sherbet soften.
Add orange juice and ginger ale.
Do not add ice.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place over low heat.
Stir until slightly soupy but not gummy.
Divide paint into as many containers as colors desired.
Add food coloring.
When cool, cover and store.
Baby food jars are ideal.
Little artists will love it.

title: coffee and cream punch
directions: Combine the coffee, ice cream and ice
milk in a mixing or punch
bowl.
Stir gently until
almost
smooth.
Stir
in ginger ale and serve immediately.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix cheese, soup and blended Ro-Tel in a heavy pan.
Add 1 cup of milk.
Cook until hot and cheese is melted.
Add milk and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until dip thickens.

title: already ready soup
directions: Place pan on burner; add stewed tomatoes and chicken broth. Bring to a boil, over high heat, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon.
Add barley, corn, beans, carrots, oregano and pepper to pan.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn off burner and serve.

title: red devil's food delight
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add wet ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into two (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll up in small balls.
Place in freezer on cookie sheet for 45 minutes, then take out and place in container.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together well. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Beat until blended.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in lightly greased pan in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots in water with no salt, just until tender.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots. Refrigerate overnight. Serve cold.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat; blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk; heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Combine with sauce in a 2-quart casserole; top with remaining cheese.
Add bread crumbs and paprika, if desired.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Wrap ham in tinfoil; place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread sliced pineapple over top.
Place in oven; cook for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; pour Coke over top of ham, rewrap, place back in oven and cook for 1 1/2 hours more.
Then remove from oven; place on platter.
Slice and serve.

title: 14 day cucumber pickles
directions: Let cucumbers and 1 pint salt in gallon boiling water stand 7 days; drain and then cover again with 1 gallon boiling water. Let set for 24 hours. Drain; add alum in 1 gallon of boiling water. Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours. Drain, wash and split cucumbers. Then fix vinegar (vinegar, sugar and spice to suit taste). Boil and pour over cucumbers; drain off for 4 days and reheat. Put in jars on 4th day and seal.

title: quick and easy carrot cake
directions: In 9-inch square pan with fork, mix well flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrots, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix briskly until thoroughly blended.
Stir in pineapple and walnuts. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
season with salt and pepper. Melt 1 stick
oleo
in
casserole;
add 1/4 remaining package stuffing and spread evenly.	Add squash mixture. Spoon it onto stuffing lining.
Sprinkle
top
with
remaining 1/4 package. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: daisy's pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar. Add eggs. Stir in pineapple. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange nut bread
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
In separate bowl, combine egg, lemon juice, oil, orange peel, orange juice and lemon peel. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Fold in walnuts.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving sizes and brown.
Add onion.
Mix the rest of the ingredients except green pepper together and pour over steak.
Add green pepper and simmer until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spread half of the mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with 1 can green chilies and grated cheese.
Spread remaining batter over top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until well browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese squash(yields 8 servings)
directions: Cut squash in small pieces; put in large skillet with butter and cook until very tender.
Place lid over skillet while cooking on medium heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat; add 1/2 package or 4 ounces soft cream cheese; stir well.
Then stir four good tablespoons of grated Cheddar cheese into mixture. Put in bowl and serve while warm.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large pot.
Almost cover with water.
Bring to boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain and add the remaining ingredients.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Pour into clean pint jars and seal.

title: grilled lemon-lime chicken
directions: Grate zest (colored part of peel) only from lemon and lime into a shallow dish.
Add juice from lemon and lime, olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Mix well.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Seal with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, turning chicken occasionally.
Brush grill with olive oil. Preheat grill.
Grill chicken over very hot coals (4 inches from coals).
Cook about 5 minutes on each side.
Serves 6.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender on high speed for about one minute.
Pour into large pie pan.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Combine melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs. Pat down.

title: spatzle(drop noodles)
directions: Bring to boiling in 3 to 4 quart saucepan 2 quarts water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Meanwhile, sift together and set aside flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine in bowl and mix together egg and 1 cup water.
Gradually add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Stir until smooth.
(Batter should be very thick and break from a spoon instead of pouring in a continuous stream.)
Spoon batter into the boiling water by 1/2 teaspoon, dipping spoon into water each time. Cook only one layer of noodles at one time; do not crowd.
After noodles rise to the surface, boil gently 5 to 8 minutes or until tender when pressed against side of pan with spoon.
Remove from water with slotted spoon, draining over water for a second and place in warm bowl.
Toss butter lightly with noodles.
Serve hot.

title: layered peach dessert
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar, pecans and flour.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Combine the cream cheese and powdered sugar; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Fold whipped topping into mixture; spread over crust.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients; cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows.
Fold over drained fruit for salad.
Add walnuts, sliced bananas and mandarin oranges.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix and chill.
Mold into a ring and fill with strawberry preserves.

title: really corny corn muffins
directions: Combine corn, water and eggs in food processor using steel blade.
Process until corn kernels are completely pureed.
Add flour; process briefly with quick, on-off motions; scraping down container until blended.
Transfer to nonstick muffin tins that have been greased.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.
Top will not brown; don't overbake.
Serve warm.

title: *pink punch*
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water, then add other ingredients.

title: healthful soup
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine with all other ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cook noodles in broth.
While noodles cook, cut chicken in bite size pieces; mix with soup and sour cream.
In a baking dish, place noodles first, then chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese; return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Grease casserole and line with tortillas.
Layer beef, chopped onion, beans, Velveeta cubes.
Repeat layers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and wash shrimp.
Add to cream cheese and mix well.
Add horseradish to taste and ketchup for color.
Great on chips and crackers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine spinach with 1/3 of the Welsh rarebit.
Top with bacon.
Spread remaining rarebit over the bacon.
Top with onions. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add chili, tomatoes and beans with juice. Cook slowly 15 minutes.
Put in 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with corn chips and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve with salad.

title: tomato soup
directions: Heat tomato juice in one pan.
Heat milk in another pan.
Add soda and salt to tomato juice.
When both pans are hot, add tomato juice to milk.
This is very important:
tomato juice to milk.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well.
Can be used with chips or vegetables.

title: chilled fruit soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, bring first 4 ingredients and 3 cups water to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch into remaining 1 cup water.
Stir into simmering mixture.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pureed peaches and juice concentrate.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Remove cinnamon stick and cloves.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with fresh fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cheese over boiling water until well blended and add everything else.
Serve in a fondue pot or a chafing dish to keep warm and dip bread cubes or whatever into dip.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine
oleo,	confectioners
sugar and peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Using toothpicks to hold balls,
dip into melted chocolate.	Place on waxed paper and refrigerate until set.

title: cajun baked beans
directions: Cook beef and sausage until done and drain. Cook bacon and crush over other meat. Drain beans. Mix meat, beans and all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese chicken with walnuts
directions: Cut chicken in thin strips; place in mixing bowl with next 6 ingredients.
Cook walnuts on medium heat in 1 teaspoon oil until gold.
Remove, sprinkle with sugar.
Cook vegetables on medium heat in 2 tablespoons oil; remove.
Cook chicken on high heat; add vegetables.
Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: mama's pork chops picante
directions: Wash and pat dry pork chops.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and dry Mexican seasoning.
Dust with flour and allow to sit in refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Pour on orange juice concentrate.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Combine
sugar, flour, soda and
pineapple.
Add
eggs, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Test with toothpick.

title: japanese pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all together and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken encore
directions: Cook chicken breasts until well done, about 40 minutes.
Cool. Remove skins and meat from the bones; cut into big cubes.
To make the sauce for the casserole, saute mushrooms in the margarine and gradually add flour, milk, chicken soup and chicken broth. Stir until thickened, then remove from the heat.

title: jalapeno bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients, in order listed, in a bowl.
Garnish with jalapeno peppers.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water and cool.
Add pineapple and cream cheese and mix.
Chill until mixture thickens.
Add Cool Whip, pecans and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Heat milk.
Add marshmallows, butter and coconut, then add rest of ingredients.
Press firmly into a stem pan that has been lined with wax paper.
Store in a cool place until firm (at least 24 hours), then turn out on a cake plate.

title: creamed sweet peas
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine flour, sugar and milk; mix well. Add peas and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until peas are heated through and sauce has thickened.	Yield:	4 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain off all cans of beans. Add onion. Mix together remainder of ingredients. Add to beans and onion. Cover; put in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Boil onion, bacon, salt and pepper until onion is soft. Preboil squash; cool and slice lengthwise.
Gut and mash.
Add to onion mixture and heat until water is gone.
Sprinkle salt on squash shells; put filling in and grate with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: round steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving-size pieces and brown on both sides in oil.
Place in roasting pan or dish.
Add onions that have been fried in oil and put on top of round steak.
Add pepper and salt (if desired), mushroom soup and water.
Soup should cover meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May add carrots and potatoes and bake another hour or until tender.
May also be served over mashed potatoes.

title: mother-in-law's favorite
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
When cake cools in a 9 x 13-inch pan, punch holes in cake with wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, then pour caramel topping over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with crushed Heath candy bars (crush candy bars in small pieces with a rolling pin before topping them on cake).

title: cajun ducks
directions: Rub ducks with bacon grease.
Season with salt and pepper. Stuff each with onion, bell pepper, apple, garlic clove and celery.
Place ducks in a Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add bouillon cubes and 1/2 cup sherry.
Cook for 2 hours on medium heat.
Take ducks out of pan.
Add green onions, mushrooms and rest of sherry to drippings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Split ducks. Serve over hot rice with sauce.

title: caraway noodles and cabbage
directions: Boil water and salt.
Add noodles and onion.
Boil gently for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 3 to 5 minutes longer or until noodles and cabbage are soft.
Drain well.
Return to pan.
Add yogurt, caraway seed and pepper.
Heat through, but don't boil.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni noodles.
Combine soup, milk, tuna, salt, pepper and cooked noodles; mix well in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chokecherry jelly
directions: Pour juice into a large heavy kettle.
Add sugar and stir to mix.
Place over high heat.
Bring to boil; stir constantly.
Stir in pectin.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir and skim for 5 minutes.
Add almond extract.
Pour into jars and seal.
Process for 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: bean hash
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain grease. Add pork and beans, diced tomatoes and onion. Simmer for 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: banana split pie
directions: In small saucepan, simmer pineapple, flour and sugar until thick.
Cool.
Line graham cracker pie crust with bananas.
