Pour pineapple mix over bananas.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries, sugar and water until tender.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add to boiled mixture.
Cool and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a mold or casserole dish.
Chill.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, onions and broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into blender and puree until smooth.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add flour and mix.
Stir in broccoli mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly and simmer for 1 minute.
This freezes beautifully.

title: brown sugar and raisin cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Dissolve baking soda in milk and add to mixture. Combine flour, salt and raisins and add to mixture. Refrigerate 4 or 5 hours. Roll into balls and press with fork. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 9 minutes. Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies, depending on size.

title: punch
directions: Mix Hawaiian Punch and ginger ale, mixing 1 bottle of ale at a time.
Mix in pineapple, tasting until it's punchy enough.
Last of all, add orange juice.
You might want to mix in 1 tablespoon of sugar.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beat after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift flours together and add gradually to mixture, mix until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nutty cinnamon ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 the nuts in a 9-inch ring mold, which has been greased.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in melted butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place 12 biscuits in ring mold.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Top with remaining coated biscuits.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn onto a serving platter.
Let pan remain for a few minutes to allow syrup to run over biscuits.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese-ham potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add flour and seasonings.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Keep stirring until bubbly.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; stir until melted.
Add ham and potatoes; toss. Spoon into greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: no-fat oatmeal cookies(no cholesterol, 65mg sodium)
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed. Add raisins. Batter will be stiff. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake in 375° oven about 10 minutes.

title: hearty tomato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook and stir onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in cream cheese.
Gradually stir in soup and milk; beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Add seasonings.
Heat, stirring frequently, but do not boil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mama's bread pudding
directions: Cube bread (removing crusts is optional).
Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Add to warm milk.
Add vanilla.
Place bread cubes in baking casserole dish.
(Optional: Toss raisins with cubes.)
Pour egg and milk mixture over bread cubes.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix (makes 10 cups).
Quick and easy and good.

title: liver nips
directions: Boil beef roast and suet until tender.
Remove from broth.
Rub with ground mustard and brown beef in oven.
Scrape liver to gristle.
Put flour in mixing bowl; add liver, eggs, salt, pepper, onion, baking powder, basil, coriander and beef broth.
Mix to a stiff dough.
Drop by tablespoon into hot broth.
Boil about 15 minutes.

title: relief from worry
directions: Sit back and close your eyes and begin rhythmic breathing. Imagine a black screen in front of your eyes.
Project on that screen some happy memory.
Call up the scenes of a favorite vacation spot or bring to mind some other pleasant occasion.
As you lead your mind from negative thoughts, you bring worry under control.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Remove from heat and blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine coconut and pecans.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Cool for at least 4 hours.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Mix well. Gently fold in whipped cream; chill. Serve with sliced ham or ham loaf.

title: ranch dressing(low-fat)
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Whisk until well blended. Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.
(The longer refrigerated flavors will blend more thoroughly.)
Yield: about one quart.

title: veg-all pot pie
directions: Combine soup, Veg-All, milk, chicken and pepper.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust and crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream
butter, egg and sugar.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add
to
mixture.
Add
vanilla.
Add enough flour to make dough, roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: aunt florie's prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together twice.
Set aside.
In a small, separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Refrigerate beaten egg whites for later.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut rings and place in ice water (approximately 2 cups), that has been sweetened with a heaping tablespoon of sugar.
Allow onions to soak in the refrigerator at least 2 hours before frying. Drain onions and dip in batter.
Fry in deep, hot oil.
Do not prepare batter until frying time.

title: buttered baked rice
directions: Soak rice in 2 cups boiling water for 15 minutes.
Drain, put rice and remaining ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Process carrots in blender or food processor until smooth.
Stir in eggs and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Serves 8. Delicious!

title: fishcamp hush puppies
directions: Add onions and salt to corn meal.
Gradually blend in water until it forms a thick mixture that can be dipped by teaspoonfuls into a deep fryer of hot oil.
(Canola is best!)
Fry until hush puppies are brown and rise to the top of the pot.
Drain well and enjoy.

title: crusty pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water; let set 5 minutes.
Add salt and oil.
Stir.
Add flour, little at a time until dough is soft and elastic.
Knead; add more flour, if needed.
Place in greased bowl. Grease top and let stand draft free for 1 hour.
Punch down and divide into 2 parts.
Press into 2 pizza pans, dusted lightly with cornmeal (may grease pans for extra crispy crust).
Add pizza ingredients and bake.

title: joanne's mock fillets
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients into balls; wrap with bacon and hold with a toothpick.
Place in casserole and brown in oven for approximately 15 to 20 minutes and pour off grease, then add the following:
mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Add enough water to make it thin enough to pour easily.
Pour sauce mixture over meatballs and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: stew meat and noodles
directions: Place stew meat in small roaster pan or large casserole; sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Add mushrooms (undrained); add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can milk.
Cover and place in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Cook noodles and add to meat mixture or serve over rice.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage with onion, garlic powder and oregano.
Drain off excess grease and add tomato paste, tomato sauce and 4 tomato sauce cans of water.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Let raisins and boiling water stand 3 hours.
Grease and flour 3 cans (No. 2 cans, Campbell's chunky soup size).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, eggs, shortening and salt.
Sift flour and soda together.
Alternate adding raisin juice and flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Fill cans.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: green misty salad
directions: Heat pineapple until hot at medium heat.
Add jello, stirring until it melts.
Add cream cheese, broken up in small pieces. Stir until melted.
Set aside and let cool until you whip Dream Whip.
Combine with gelatin mixture and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: healthful mustard
directions: Blend lemon juice, salt, turmeric and soy flour.
Pour into saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool.
Return to blender and add, while whizzing garlic and oil.
Chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put the frozen vegetables in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours to thaw.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup of the Swiss cheese. Top the casserole with the 1/2 cup Swiss cheese and remaining onion rings. Bake at 375° until bubbles.

title: sea breeze salad
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients with cooked shells.
Mix well. Chill.
Toss before serving.

title: fiesta chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
In a 3-quart pot, place chili seasoning, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans and garlic salt. Add meat; bring mixture to boiling.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in olives and heat a few minutes longer.
Serve topped with a dollop of sour cream and chopped green onion.
Makes 6 servings. Good served with corn muffins or corn chips and lettuce wedges with a creamy dressing.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Make jello as directed on the box. Chill. Add cranberries. Add cream cheese (cut up into small pieces). Add celery and nuts, if desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Before baking, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, mixed.
Use muffin cups; they freeze well.
Makes about 20 muffins.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat at medium speed with electric mixer.
Shape into ball, cover and chill.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Combine zucchini, bread crumbs, mayonnaise, seasoning, egg and onions.
Shape into patties.
Roll in flour.
Saute in oil until browned.

title: philly cream cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Crust:
Crush about 36 graham crackers to make 3 cups crumbs. Add 6 tablespoons sugar and stir 2/3 cup melted butter or margarine in.
Press into pie dishes and freeze or buy already made.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine salmon and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
To make full loaf pan, double recipe.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil, then add your flour.
Add eggs one at a time.
Grease cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: deep dish egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and salt until smooth.
Use whisk beater. Add one egg at a time; mix well.
Beat in milk and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Cook noodles in chicken stock; let noodles soak up as much broth as they will.
Saute celery, onions and pepper in oleo.
Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 325° until heated thoroughly. Freezes well.

title: diet turkey lasagna
directions: Combine all ingredients, except uncooked noodles and cheese. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer 5 uncooked noodles in pan; add the remaining mixture and sprinkle cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb dinner rolls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add hot water.
Stir until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Knead with floured hands for 5 minutes until smooth.
Add more flour if needed to reduce stickiness.
Cover and let rest 5 minutes.
Grease two large cookie sheets.
Shape dough into 16 to 18 balls and place on cookie sheets.
Let rise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes, in a warm place. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dishrag pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and spices in a large pan.
Peel the cucumbers and cut into quarters (lengthwise).
Remove seeds from cucumbers (a grapefruit spoon is ideal for this job!).
Cut the extra long pieces in half.
Add the cucumbers to the vinegar-sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until they seem a little soft (being careful not to overcook them as they will become mushy).
Pack in jars and cover with hot liquids. Seal.

title: baked cream cheese appetizer
directions: Unroll dough on a lightly floured surface and press seams together to form a 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle cream cheese block with dill weed and gently press it in.
Place cheese, dill weed side down, in center of dough.
Bring up sides of dough snugly around cheese, pinching to seal.

title: shrimp and fresh vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients from tomatoes to fresh basil in bowl and let set at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours.
Saute carrots, celery and eggplant in skillet.
Cook linguine.
Add cleaned shrimp to skillet; as soon as shrimp turn pink, remove from heat. When linguine is ready to serve, drain and toss with tomato and cheese mixture and hot skillet contents.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Mix other ingredients together in baking pan.
Put pork chops on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: butterscotch pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk.
Cook over moderate heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add a small amount to beaten yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute.
Add butter, vanilla and butterscotch pieces.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: chicken wing appetizers
directions: Cut wings into 3 pieces, discarding wing tip pieces.
Place remaining pieces in foil-lined 15 x 8-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Brush over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, turning chicken and basting with sauce frequently.
Serves 12.

title: macaroni-sausage supper
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook meat and onion until sausage is browned.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat through.
Serves 2.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add eggs (slightly beaten) and cheese to hot grits.
Stir until mixed well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole or oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom pasta olio
directions: Saute onions, garlic and peppers in a few tablespoons of olive oil on medium heat for two minutes.
Add more oil or chicken broth and mushrooms and sun-dried tomatoes and saute only until they are still crispy.
Add chopped spinach, precooked pasta and additional olive oil and continue tossing until hot.

title: delightful date bars
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add rest of the dry ingredients.
Use large (13 x 9-inch) pan.
Grease well.
Use 1/2 of the dry mixture and spread in cake pan.
Pat down well.
Spread out the date mixture on top.
Then follow with rest of the dry mixture.
Pat down lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slightly beaten eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix with spoon.
Pour into greased, floured oblong pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chive dressing
directions: Whirl
or
process
ingredients until smoothly blended. If made
ahead,
shake well before using.
Use over vegetables of your choice.
Can top salad with crumbled Blue cheese too.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill before serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, eggs and milk.
Add pineapple and juice and mix well.
Add bread and mix until liquid is soaked into bread. Bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
You can use less sugar.

title: linda's yellow cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on box for Bundt recipe.
Bake in Bundt pan.
Remove from pan.

title: cream cheese-meat pinwheel appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
The small amount of milk helps to mix.
2 pkg. dried beef slivered.
Take the dried beef, lay each piece flat.
Using a knife spread mixture (generous amount) on each slice.
Roll these slices into individual rolls and refrigerate until firm.
Remove and cut into 1 inch pieces.
Serve using toothpicks.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Cream cheese with salad dressing.
Add pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheezy beer bread
directions: Mix until moistened.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Tastes good toasted.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Use with any fresh veggies.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add cooked raisins and stir good. Add sifted ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and whole kernel corn. Drain the zucchini and corn. Mix eggs, onion, milk and salt. Pour egg mixture over zucchini and corn in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake in covered, greased casserole 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Can be microwaved for 20 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish, top with Ritz cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine.
Cook about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fruit for a southern brunch
directions: Drain fruit; mix well with sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Place in greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Top with oatmeal mixed with flour and dash of salt.
Top with 1/2 cup margarine that has been cut up into small squares.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: meat noodle kugel
directions: Add all ingredients to the cooked noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into very hot well-greased pan.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Top will be brown.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat butter 30 seconds in an 8-inch round dish. Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Blend together butter, brown sugar and drained pineapple. Spread evenly in bottom of dish.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, substituting the reserved pineapple juice for water.
Pour batter evenly over pineapple mixture. Cook 5 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time. Rest 5 minutes until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Invert onto serving dish.

title: potato chips cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Shape in small balls and press lightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: icing for sweet potato cake
directions: Cream
oleo and cream cheese until smooth; add vanilla. Gradually add powdered
sugar
and beat until creamy.
Stir in nuts.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: chocolate sin in a bowl
directions: Prepare brownie mix and pudding according to package directions.
Crumble brownies and Heath bars separately.

title: oven steak
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak.
Brown in hot fat.
Arrange pepper rings, paper thin slices of lemon and slices of onion around top of steak.
Put mushrooms on top of the steak.
Cook covered in slow oven (275° or 300°) for at least 1 1/2 hours, adding small amounts of water when needed.

title: green pea guacamole
directions: Drain and chill peas or beans.
Combine all in a blender, except lime juice.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Transfer to serving container.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in lime juice.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add 1/2 dry ingredients sifted together.
Add mincemeat and nuts; then add rest of dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "granny's" smothered liver and onions with gravy
directions: Note:
Be sure the liver is trimmed and gristle cut out.

title: bean salad
directions: Put all cans of beans in freezer 1 hour before you make the salad. This prevents them from falling apart when mixing. Mix all ingredients together and store in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Saute shrimp and onion together for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add together mushrooms, salt, flour, cayenne pepper and sour cream. Lower heat until warm.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Divide into 2 parts and put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: picadillo con alcaparras (picadillo with capers)(best translation for picadillo is spanish beef hash)
directions: Use a large skillet with cover.
Heat olive oil and brown beef in hot oil until red of the meat disappears.
Combine onion, green pepper, tomato, garlic, bay leaf, crushed oregano and capers.
Add to meat in skillet. Mix well and cook covered for about 10 minutes on moderate heat.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up, wash and drain cauliflower.
Mix all together.
Chill in fridge before serving.

title: sliced apple cake
directions: Mix together salad oil and sugar.
Add apples in eggs and vinegar.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add these to first mixture and beat.
Add 1 cup nuts. Bake in a slow oven at 350° until done.

title: jiffy crab casserole
directions: Melt butter, milk and cheese together in large saucepan or microwave.
Mix with crabmeat and noodles.
Place mixture in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with croutons.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bea's treasure cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add crumbs and mix well.
Add Eagle Brand milk, butter, and vanilla. Mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12-14 minutes.
Do not over cook.

title: baklava
directions: Mix chopped nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar together.
Grease a large 11 x 16 inch pan with melted butter.
Place 6 fila in pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Sprinkle with thin layer of nuts and cover with 3 fila, brushing each with melted butter. Alternate in this way until nuts and fila are used, topping with 6 butter fila.
Cut pastry into small diamond shapes.
Bake in slow oven - 300° - for 1 1/2 hours until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool.
Pour warm syrup over pastry.

title: ratatouille
directions: Prepare cubed eggplant.
Prepare sliced zucchini.
Cook all ingredients in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender.
Serves 6.

title: lemon jello pudding cake
directions: Put everything in bowl except eggs.
Mix and add 1 egg at a time.
Add bits after all is mixed and in tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350 degree oven.
Bake in greased tube cake pan.

title: stuffed vienna bread
directions: Cut bread 3/4 the way down.
Mix next 5 ingredients together. Stuff the bread with cheese, then mushrooms and onion.
Pour butter mixture over stuffed bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake top pudding
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in milk.
Blend in slivered almonds.
Beat the egg whites until stiff. Fold into mixture.

title: applesauce meat balls
directions: Beat egg with milk.
Add croutons; let stand until soft.
Beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; combine thoroughly. Shape into 24 balls.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine soup and water; pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Mix eggs, vinegar and water.
Blend together; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll out.
May be frozen unbaked.
Makes 12.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef and drain.
Add green pepper and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in water, paste and sauce mix. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle parmesan over bottom of frozen pie crust.
Spread meat mixture with 1 c. mozzarella. Repeat layers except mozzarella.
Bake 15 minutes.
Top with mozzarella.
Return to oven and melt cheese.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine lemon jello, cold water, eggs and oil.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Empty cake mix in bowl; beat 1 minute.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and prick full of holes with fork.
Combine confectioners sugar and juice of lemons.
Pour over hot cake.

title: apple brownies
directions: Slice apples thin.
Combine sugar with oleo and eggs.
Add all the dry ingredients.
The mixture will be thick.
Fold in apple slices.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Serve squares plain, with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cook dates, 1/2 cup sugar and water until thick; cool.
Cream shortening and rest of sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Divide dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Spread 1/2 mixture over dough.
Roll like jelly roll. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Place on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and corn flakes.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Pour butter over top; sprinkle corn flakes over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: delicious sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine juice, tapioca and cinnamon.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add apple slices and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into prepared unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Glaze top crust with egg white mixture (1 egg white mixed with 2 tablespoons water).
Bake at 350° or 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm with ice cream.
(I use Guilt Free No Fat, No Sugar vanilla ice cream.)

title: biscuits
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cut into biscuits.
Pour butter over before baking.
Bake at 500° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook milk until scalded.
Mix flour and sugar; add to hot milk until thickened.
Beat egg yolks and add to custard.
Add salt, vanilla, butter or oleo and coconut.
Pour in shell and cool.
When serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Break tuna into pieces with fork.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over direct heat, then stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and milk and cook over boiling water while stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Add chicken and stir until blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in soup bowls topped with a garnish of chopped chives.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan. Add celery and mushrooms. Cook slowly for about 5 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and chicken broth gradually, stirring constantly. Cook until sauce is thickened. Stir in chopped chicken. Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.

title: mexican-style liver
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Take out bacon and drain all but 3 tablespoons of grease.
Cook onion in grease until tender.
Combine flour, chili powder and salt.
Cut liver in thin strips and roll in flour mixture.
Cook all the liver, stir in crumbled bacon.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks of margarine and pour over top of cake, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I like it best served warm.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of deep bowl.
In layers, add celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Do not toss.
Spread real mayonnaise evenly over layers of peas.
Sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle bacon over salad before serving.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Place all ingredients, except bread crumbs, into a food processor.
Process until totally blended.
Add bread crumbs until mixture gets too thick to process.
Remove from processor and mix in more bread crumbs until mixture becomes thick enough to form a ball.
Place formed balls on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put crushed pineapple evenly over this.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the cake mix over this.
Then layer pie filling over that.
Sprinkle the rest of the cake mix over the filling.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the cake mix and then drizzle 1 stick
of melted margarine evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter munchies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, peanut butter and oleo; use a wooden spoon.
Roll between palms to shape into small balls.
Roll half in nuts and half in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Combine peanut butter and chocolate syrup in glass bowl. Microwave on High for 2 minutes; mix well.
Place in paper bag; add confectioners sugar, nuts and candies.
Shake until cereal is coated with confectioners sugar.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine all and mix well.

title: black beans and yellow rice
directions: Make rice as label directs.
In last 5 minutes of cooking, add beans and salsa.
Allow to rest for 5 minutes.
Top with chopped scallions, tomato or pimento.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves 5 minutes. Combine beef, bread cubes, salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion and eggs.
Form meat mixture into 10 to 12 oblong patties.
Place a meat patty on each of the cabbage leaves. Roll in cabbage leaf and fasten leaves to meat with toothpicks.
Place stuffed leaves in cold electric skillet. Pour undiluted tomato soup over them.
Cover and cook on low heat (260°) for 45 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: microwave potato salad(prep time: 20 minutes plus chilling; microwave time: 18 minutes)
directions: Place potatoes and water in 3-quart casserole.
Cover. Microwave on High 16 to 18 minutes or until tender, stirring after 9 minutes; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "no fail" pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Beat egg, vinegar and water together and add to dry ingredients.
Makes 5 shells.
May be frozen for later use.

title: julie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Roll into balls; flatten balls with hand.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Prepare peppers.
Cut off tops.
Remove seeds.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes in salted water.
Drain and put in flat baking dish. Combine rice, beef and crackers.
Add 1/2 cheese and 1/2 tomato sauce-water mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon into peppers.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese and drizzle with rest of tomato sauce.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: If you wish the soup to cook quickly, soak the peas in water overnight.
Drain.
Put peas and ham in water.
Add onions and celery.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly, stirring occasionally, until peas have disintegrated and turned to mush.
Add seasonings to taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on pan and move to cooling racks.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, a little at a time.
Add warm milk, a little at a time.
Stir in salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 10 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Combine curry powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over chicken, rub seasoning onto top and bottom surfaces of each piece of chicken and set aside.
In 10-inch skillet, combine orange juice, rice, water, brown sugar, mustard and remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt; mix well.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand covered until liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cascade salad
directions: Put yogurt in mixing bowl. Stir cranberries, hazelnuts, salmon and carrots into yogurt. Fold mixture into bowl of fresh, tossed garden greens. Serve as salad meal with hot, fresh bread or toast.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend butter, sugars, nuts and vanilla into grated potatoes; fold in beaten eggs.
Pour into well-greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
May be served warm, or cooled and served topped with whipped cream. Yields 8 servings.

title: no fail custard pie
directions: Combine in blender and mix well.
Pour into well-greased pie plate (large).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake another 30 minutes.
This pie has no crust, but is rather crusty on top.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: make ahead meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add the next 5 ingredients. Add beef. Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls, about 12 dozen. Place in single layers in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until no longer pink, turning often. Drain. Cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Jell-O pudding in a bowl.
Add pineapple and mix.
Add marshmallows and pecans last.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until brown.
Drain.
Put in pie plate.
Beat milk.
Mix eggs, salt and pepper until smooth. Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese. Continue baking until knife in center comes out clean (5 to 8 minutes).
Remove and let cool.

title: triple chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add eggs and milk to dry mix.
Don't overmix.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of the whipped topping. Stir in 3/4 cup of the strawberries.
Pour into pie crust; chill until firm, about 15 minutes.

title: sunshine biscuits
directions: Lay each biscuit on cookie sheet.
Make indention with thumb in center of each biscuit.
Fill with a few drops of preserves. Take a knife and draw lines from center outward for rays of sun. Bake according to package directions.
Add a little sunshine to your morning!

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together.
Pour 3 ounces of batter in greased or paper lined muffin pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Remove.
Cool and serve.

title: stacked tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper on top of tomatoes.
Spread mayonnaise over top, then green onions.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over last.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan, crumbling in pieces. Drain grease. Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with butter. Tear bread with crusts in small pieces and place in bottom of prepared pan (like stuffing). Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Beat 6 eggs with milk and pour over sausage and bread.
Sprinkle cheese on. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in berries and nuts, wheat germ and orange peel.
Combine egg white, juice, water and oil with flour mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten well.
Bake in bread loaf pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, creamed corn, cooking oil, corn bread mix and sugar. Fold
in sour cream.
Bake in a 10 x 13-inch oiled pan 30 minutes at 400°.

title: warm cranberry punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice, orange juice and honey into large saucepan.
Add cinnamon stick and cloves.
Simmer juice for 15 minutes.
Stir few times with mixing spoon.
Let punch cool for 10 minutes.
Put strainer over punch bowl.
Pour punch slowly into bowl through strainer.
Discard cloves and cinnamon stick.
Add 1 quart lemon-lime soda at room temperature to the punch.
Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: indiana cream pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour and eggs.
(May use blender.)
Add vanilla.
Slowly add half and half; mix well.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Then bake at 350° until top is brown and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sizzle cakes
directions: Mix all into batter.
Use a paper funnel and pour into hot oil in swirling design.
Turn only once; place on paper towels.
While hot, dust with powdered sugar.

title: quick tuna dinner
directions: Cook noodles about 5 minutes.
Cook celery in oil until golden.
Add peas, salt, pepper and tuna, drained.
Mix.
Arrange noodles (drained) around edge of skillet; put tuna mixture in center and pour tomato sauce over tuna mix.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: raw relish
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers, carrots and onions and add salt.
Mix well and let stand 3 hours.
Let drain 1 hour.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix and let stand 1/2 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sweet potato hash
directions: Cover potatoes, water and salt in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Drain immediately, and cover with cold water; drain.
Pat dry, or let stand 15 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in a saucepan large enough to serve as a mixing bowl; remove from the stove.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs (one at a time), vanilla, nuts and flour.
Mix well. Spread mixture in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for about 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: chocolate-chip pound cake
directions: Mix
in
large	mixing	bowl, the cake mix, pudding and oil. Add
eggs,	one
at a time, beating after each addition. Add milk; fold in chocolate chips and grated chocolate.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes (or until done) in a Bundt or tube pan. Cool slightly.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, measure all ingredients except oats.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until blended.
Stir in oats. Drop dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven until golden brown. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: hershey's chocolate peppermint log
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jellyroll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, with aluminum foil; generously grease pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.

title: thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat Crisco and brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and salt; mix well.
Add nuts; mix.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press centers with thumb; fill with favorite preserves (apricot, strawberry and raspberry are very good).
Combination of preserves makes a nice looking pattern. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen.

title: extra crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, oil, salt, vanilla and other extract.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar in bowl.
Add to first mixture.
Mix until smooth; roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy wine cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased angel pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not turn pan upside down.
Cool; put on plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: orange rolls
directions: Mix scalded milk, margarine, sugar and salt together and cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water. When milk mixture is cool, add remaining ingredients and mix well. Knead for 5 to 10 minutes. Let rise (approximately 2 hours).
Punch down.
Form into desired shape and let rise again. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Dice all of the ingredients and combine in a large bowl or container.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: green chile 'n cheese biscuit bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place one biscuit in center of pan, arrange other biscuits in a circle, edges touching the center biscuit.
Press dough out to 10-inch circle.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple and cold water. Pour into baking dish.
Put marshmallows on top and refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Beat eggs and milk with mixer until blended.
Beat in mayonnaise, onion, soup and cheese.
With spoon, stir in broccoli until all are well blended.
Place in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, until set and lightly browned.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well.
Pour and stir while cooking.
When thickens, dump on board and knead when cool enough to handle.
